column6: Crest Pro-Health HD Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Healthier Mouth via Daily Two-Step System - 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
column13: Crest Pro Health HD is easy and works
column14: I received Crest Pro Health HD from BzzAgent to try for free and have been using it for a couple weeks now and I love this product. You only have two steps to whiten your teeth and in reality you are only brushing your teeth twice. The first step is to brush with the cleaning toothpaste, which tastes just like crest toothpaste. The second step is to brush again with the whitening toothpaste, which also tastes a bit like crest toothpaste, and a bit more jelly like but it didn't bother me at all. And that is it. After a week of using Crest Pro Health HD I noticed a difference in my smile and teeth color, and now after 4 weeks, I have noticed a huge difference....my teeth are really white and other people are even noticing. I recommend this product for anyone that wants an easy way to whiten your smile without jumping through the hoops other products want you to do. I really liked that you didn't have to keep the product away from your lips while using it. I have used whiteners in the past that burn your lips if it gets on them. This system is really easy an yields great results. I got Crest Pro Health HD free to try from BzzAgent, but I have already gone out and purchased another one and have made it a part of my daily routine.

column13: Cooks, mixes and feels cleaner than any coconut oil I have previously used - and now kills cancer too! Awesome
column14:
Coconut Oil is turning out to be the real deal. Of the ton of articles I have read about it the following is a summary of what is going on.

Lauric acid (coconut oil is about 50% lauric acid) killed over 93% of human colon cancer cells (Caco-2) after 48 hours of treatment. Intriguingly, the lauric acid poisoned the cancer cells by simultaneously unleashing profound oxidative stress while strongly reducing their levels of glutathione (which is exactly what the cancer cells needed to protect themselves from the increased oxidative stress).

It has been shown to raise levels of the beneficial cholesterol HDL in women, improve their LDL:HDL ratio, and resulted in superior weight loss and abdominal fat lass compared to soybean oil. Coconut oil is now being used in clinical trials for improving cholesterol in patients with chronic heart disease,

It is being used in trials to fighting Alzheimerâ€™s, for improving blood pressure and blood sugar levels.

Coconut oil is unique in that it is about 50% lauric acid, a medium chained triglyceride that is otherwise very hard to find in our diets (palm kernel oil is also about 50% lauric acid). Interestingly, lauric acid makes up about 2% of the fat in cowâ€™s milk but 6% of the fat in human milk, implying that humans may have a naturally higher need for this fatty acid.

I was so pumped by all these studies that I have been using coconut oil for awhile but when I saw this RAW, Extra virgin oil I knew I had to try it. It cooks cleaner than my current organic oil and smells better too. I recently acquired some essential peppermint oil and mixed it with the Coco & Co. Extra Virgin Coconut oil (since it is a carrier or base oil) to make some lotion. Since this coconut oil goes from liquid to cream to liquid it made quick work of making a homemade lotion. My first attempt and it was pretty decent.

I love that this oil is RAW and super pure because the quality is just so much better than the "big box" organic club brand I had been using. Makes me wonder how organic it really was. I look forward to less struggle with my cholesterol. It was getting better even with the other coconut oil but should be even better now since I use this oil so much more than the other. I hope my blood pressure goes to normal. The last readings were encouraging after using Coco & Co. for just a short time. I cannot wait to see the long term results!

column6: Vitamin C Serum 20 for Face with Hyaluronic Acid & Vitamin E Oil, that Helps Fade Age Spots, Clear Adult Acne & Get Rid of Wrinkles for a Glowing & Younger Looking Skin
column14:
How do you compare the hundreds of skin care products? As a regular tester, I've arrived at a list of key considerations. I hope these are helpful to you!

~ Fragrance: Citrus-cinnamon scent. No added fragrance.
~ Feel during application: Wet and smooth. This has the texture of a very thick serum or uber-light moisturizer.
~ Feel after absorption: Soft, no film or greasy feeling left behind.
~ Is it best for a certain skin type?: Should be okay for all. No problems with my sensitive, oily skin.
~ Is it tested on animals?: No.
~ Packaging: 1oz airless pump, pump is precise and easy to control.
~ Immediate cosmetic effects:* Skin looks slightly smoother and moister.
~ Potential long-term effectiveness:* Has several good active ingredients for wrinkles and inflammation. I would not rely on this as your only active anti-aging product, but itâ€™s one of the more pleasing vitamin C/hyaluronic acid formulations Iâ€™ve used in terms of how it feels on the skin. It's free of silicone fillers and contains almost all natural ingredients.

*Know the difference between cosmetic and long-term effects: Cosmetic effects are immediate and only present when the product has been applied recently - just like makeup. Long-term effects take longer to see and should remain when you stop using the product (but don't when you find something effective - your skin needs continuing support). The ideal product would be both cosmetically and long-term effective, but it's more realistic to expect a formula to tilt towards one or the other.

I received this free or virtually so for product testing and review. I am under no obligation to provide a positive review and receive no incentives or rewards for doing so. My aim is to highlight features and drawbacks that I would want to know about as a buyer, not hype the product for the manufacturer. My remarks are sincere and my own.

column13: Very Thick, Probably Great for Very Dry Hair
column14:
OGX Awapuhi Ginger Conditioner smells wonderful but does leave my hair feeling heavy and a little greasy. I'm a huge fan of OGX brand shampoo/conditioner in general and have loved almost all of the ones I've tried but with thick hair that builds oil quickly, the Repairing Awapuhi Ginger conditioner just wasn't for me. If you have exceptionally dry hair and need a heavier, more moisturizing conditioner then this may be perfect for you.

Overall I highly recommend the OGX brand if you're looking for a more natural, environmentally friendly product. They DON'T test on animals and most of their shampoos and conditioners are free of parabens, sulfates or other harsh chemicals which is great for you and for your hair. Keep in mind, that you won't get the silicon-ey soft feel that chemical-laden conditioners leave your hair with, but after a while your hair will be healthier and stronger on its own and less weighed down with gunk.

column14:
I have long, thick hair and, being from the microwave generation, do not want to spend a lot of time getting it dry. This inexpensive Revlon hair dryer had it all - strong air flow, and hot heat. So many other hair dryers have one or the other - being blasted by arctic air doesn't do much to dry my hair in a quick manner, and putting out a wimpy air flow that is hot enough to melt steel doesn't speed up the drying process as much as you'd think, either. I was so excited when I got this dryer, as I could get my completely dry in under ten minutes (again, long and thick!)

I bought this in August 2013. I am coming to leave a review today, because this hair dryer died as spectacularly as it lived. It spit fire at me, and then died. RIP little dryer. I hope your replacement is as wonderful as you were.

I originally search Amazon.com for a deodorant my friend recommended called PiperWai. The search results gave me Schmidts. Amazon does not carry PiperWai. Ultimately I decided to try both. I used to Schmidts for several weeks before the PiperWai arrived, and to my delight Schmidt's works beautifully.  I was a little concerned about the baking soda in Schmidt's because I once made my own deodorant using baking soda, and it gave me a terrible, painful rash. But Schmid's has not done that! So then my PiperWai arrived. I tried PiperWai out for a few days, and it was apparent it did not work as well for me as Schmidt's. I had odor half way through the day. I am not knocking it though because I suppose it could be reapplied, and it smells wonderful. Now my husband is using the PiperWai, and it works well for him! But for me, Schmidt's is the winner!

column6: SpaWorks Konjac Exfoliating Facial Cleansing Sponge - 2 pack - Feel Beautiful
column13: Super soft exfoliating facial cleansing sponge!
column14:
Each of the two exfoliating facial cleansing sponges are individually packaged with the instructions printed on the package. It is easy to use, just soak it so that it comes soft and puffy, and it is ready to use. After re-hydrating the sponge, I was curious to see if there was an odor or off-putting scent associated with the sponge but thankfully it did not smell like anything at all.

For myself, I squirted a bit of my facial cleanser on top of the sponge and started wiping the konjac sponge in circular motions around my face. Basing on the appearance, I thought the sponge would be rough. However, it certainly was not the case with this konjac sponge, it was very soft and it didn't feel like I was rubbing anything onto my face with how gentle it was. It was definitely a pleasant surprise and I bet I cleaned my face longer than usual because of how comfortable and soft it was. After cleansing my face, I rinsed the konjac sponge to get the excess cleaner out and squeezed it to dry it out. The sponge is attached to a string in which you can use to hang dry for your next use.

I definitely recommend this sponge for people who want to have a better cleansing ritual. Usually I wash my face with the facial cleanser and hands and I hope to see and feel the difference with this sponge.

column6: Raw African Black Soap Imported From Ghana 1lb.
column13: A little goes a long way.
column14:
FYI: Authentic African Black Soap is not supposed to be black. It is supposed to be brown. Soaps claiming to be ABS and are black are not authentic, even though they may work perfectly fine for some people. They are typically just dyed soaps. If those products work for you, then great! If you want the authentic stuff, this is it.
Before I tried this soap, I tried Dudu Osun for several months. It's authentic, but it's been formed into soap bars, which some people might not like. While that soap is great, I wanted to get something that would last longer rather than buying bars of soap. I'm so glad that I bought this because it was totally worth it. While Dudu Osun is great, it felt a bit stronger for my face (I have combination and sometimes hypersensitive skin; I'm also African American with brown skin around Gabrielle Union's color maybe...I wear NW45 in MAC and Golden Deep in BareMinerals foundation if that gives you a better idea) and had a slight fragrance whereas this stuff makes my skin feel less tight after cleansing, and there is no slight fragrance. There is a slight scent to this one, but it's not as strong as Dudu Osun. The package came in a plastic wrap when I opened the box and WOW. This block is huge, and the soap is malleable, meaning that you can pull it apart and break it into pieces if you want.It's almost kinda squishy. I really love how little pieces last forever. Like with any ABS, it will dissolve in water if you let it sit in it; if you like to melt it down or make your own liquid soap, then this is great but if you want to avoid any melting, then store it in a soap dish.
This soap is drying, but it is tolerable as long as you have a very good moisturizer. Sometimes I wash my face with a few drops of tea tree oil and this soap in order to remove some dark spots, but that is more of a personal thing I like to do. By itself, it's very good for drying out blemishes. If you're looking for deep exfoliation, this soap is great for that; youcould even take it a step further and use an exfoliation pad. There are some tiny grains in mine, but they haven't hurt me like some people have complained. I haven't found any hairs in my batch either. I've had this soap for a little over a month and still have about 80-90% of it left, but this is only because a little goes a very long way. I'll definitely purchase this again. It's cost-effective and works incredibly well.

column6: Anti Cellulite Hot Cream From Uptown Cosmeceuticals Reduces Appearance of Cellulite, Promotes Supple & Toned Skin, Muscle Relaxer, Great Alternatives to Expansive Treatment, 4 Fl. Oz
column13: Silky smooth skin is a great bonus when you use this Hot Jelly!
column14:
This Hot Jelly from Uptown Cosmeceuticals does live up to its name. The product looks like an Orange Creamsicle in cream form but smells like a combo of Vicks VapoRub and Mint. Since it is a scent I grew up with I did not mind it at all. I actually chose this product because of its claim of being a muscle relaxant and for that it works very well. My experience is that the cream went on a bit cool and then it gets "minty fresh" which some might call "heat". There is nothing that can burn you so the "heat" is actually not hot to the touch but like Tiger Balm and other products, it has such an intense cooling sensation that it can almost be called "hot" if that makes sense. It does relax the muscles but more interestingly is what it does to the skin after it put on and dries. The skin is silky soft and smooth. I was really surprised about this and loved the effect. The scent lingers for a bit but is not overpowering like when you first put it on and it is wet.

I RECEIVED THIS PRODUCT AT A DISCOUNTED RATE IN EXCHANGE FOR TESTING AND REVIEW. This is my personal experience with Uptown Cosmeceuticals Hot Jelly.

column6: eb5 Intense Moisture Anti-Aging Cream
column13: Not for those with sensitive skin or sensitivity to mineral oil.
column14:
I am always looking for great moisturizers for sensitive skin and was excited to get this to review through the Amazon Vine program. It ended up causing horrible breakouts on my face after only a couple days of use and I had to discontinue using it.

This is a very nice smooth cream. It absorbed quickly into the skin and my skin felt nice and smooth after using it. I used it both before bed and under my makeup in the morning. It was really a great moisturizer to use under my makeup; having it on made my makeup go on smoother and last longer.

Unfortunately I started to get red bumps all over my forehead and cheeks a couple days after using it. It was awful and it's taken a couple weeks to recover from. I was really disappointed because I loved how it went on under my makeup without looking greasy.

I am guessing the main culprit is the mineral oil, whose main purpose is to sit on your skin and prevent moisture from leaving your skin. Unfortunately as a side effect it can cause bacteria to build up on the surface of your skin. I've had trouble with mineral oil based products before and wish I would have seen that that was one of the main ingredients in this before trying it.

I think this product will work well for some people. However those with sensitive skin (especially sensitivity to mineral oil) should look elsewhere. I am going to continue to use my Acure Day Cream. The Acure Day Cream smells great and has actually significantly improved my skin quality and reduced wrinkling.

column14: As a mommy of 2 who breastfed for greater than a year with each, I had my fair share of thinning hair. Post pregnancy, my fear was to loose hair, but it was inevitable. 3 months after the birth of my baby, my hair started to shed in the handfuls with each shower. While, I never give in to "quick fixes," I was desperate to try something to cut down on the hair loss. Ultrax Labs Hair Surge Caffeine Shampoo intrigued me and I'm glad I gave it a fair shot. After using this product for almost a month, the amount of hair that is loss with each shower has greatly declined. I can run my fingers through my hair and finger comb my hair, without seeing strands of hair in my hand. There is much more vibrance to my hair and managability with use of Ultrax, which in my case, is usually obtained with rotating several shampoos. The smell of the shampoo is very invigorating, smells almost of tea tree oil. My only complaint is that this shampoo does not produce a foaming lather, however, using 4-5 pumps is ample to shampoo my hair. Otherwise, this product is a keeper, I already ordered my next bottle!

column6: Perfect Brows (TM) Botanical Primer and Care Balm with Mini-Brush O.6 oz/18 ml
column13: Really a great product. Seems like this is going to last ...
column14:
Really a great product. Seems like this is going to last me a while as well. I keep forgetting to put it on every night...but that's generally when I apply. I've also worn this UNDERNEATH my eyebrow pencil but logically, since growth hormone is highest at night, it makes sense to nourish that growth when you go to bed. In the morning, I wake up and there is no serum wiped onto my sheets but I imagine if you put a lot (which isn't necessary) it could potentially (?)

The only thing I can say is that the color is listed here as dark brown so I was under the impression that this would replace the need for me to pencil in my brows. That's NOT the case!!! It's quite light, it's a serum! You can tell from other customer review photos. Another thing I love is that it's not waxy and it's very easy to apply so it will not pull out any existing growth we want to hold onto!! :)

I've been using the product for perhaps a month and a half and have forgotten some nights and I DO NOTICE A DIFFERENCE! My brows are so sparse so I'll be sticking to tweezing very minimally and then using hair shears to trim my brows into a pleasing shape. I don't think I'll be returning to get my eyebrows threaded or waxed again.

column13: Whiten your teeth every night with ease
column14: I have been using Crest 3D White Brilliance Daily Cleansing now for 3 weeks and it truly does whiten your teeth.  I will say its more of a gradual whitening instead of the more powerful effect you get with the strips.  After the first week my spouse started to notice it and my friends noticed in about two weeks.  Basically you are now brushing your teeth for 2 mins total (which helps right off the bat), 1 min. with the first deep cleaning toothpaste and 1 min. with the whitening system.  This product from crest does not leave my mouth feeling raw or pealing like some other brands have done to me in the past.  Overall I am impressed with it and will buy it again; however maybe not all the time.  I will say its more work than doing the whitening strips, but its also not as expensive considering replaces your regular toothpaste and overall cost is lower.  I would recommend it for anyone to at lest try if you have a big event coming up (just leave yourself 4 weeks advance time).  Thank you to Crest for allowing me to try this product for free.

column6: Yes To Tomatoes 3-Step Acne Fighting and Clear Skin Regimen
column14:
I want to thank you from the bottom of my heart for your Yes-To-Tomatoes line. Just a week and a half ago, my skin was a mess- like I cried about it mess! I've struggled with acne for a long time! I've tried lots of programs from Proactive (which I instantly regretted because it reeks havoc on your skin and natural moisture barrier), to Ole Henrickson, to Peter Thomas Roth, to Mario Badescu ( I still use some of his spot treatments), to buying a clarisonic... To enrolling in PocketDerm to get a prescription, to bathing my skin in honey--- I've tried everything. On a whim, I picked up your kit in Target, thinking, what's another twenty bucks on acne stuff. Acne has really been breaking my bank but it is my largest insecurity.
The entire part of my lower face was broken out in small cystic acne. It was painful and grotesque to look at. I had acne in my brows (just a couple). I decided to jump in with two feet and try the system out. I also purchased the face wipes from this line.
First off I loved the way all three products felt. Your products do really well to balance each other and my face didn't feel tight and your moisturizer (which my boyfriend says smells like cinnamon rolls) is SO hydrating. Second, with in a couple days my skin was BRIGHTER and my acne was healing. My pores have shrunk and while I'm still breaking out in a couple areas it is a huge improvement. I hope that my continued use will keep my skin clear.
Thank you for such an easy, affective, and affordable system that is also not chalked full of unnatural ingredients.
I hope to be able to purchase more products soon, I'm looking at your spot treatment and mud mask especially!
I worked in beauty retail for a year and a half and have tried almost every system (slowly and one at a time)-- this is THE BEST system I have ever used. I am getting the same results I saw when I had a two week prescription to clyndamicin. It made me cry again--- but with happiness.
THANK YOU FORTHE BEST SKIN I'VE HAD IN 4 YEARS

column6: [MIZON] All in One Snail Repair Cream 75ml
column14:
So far, this is really, really nice!

First of all, shipping: I had no issues with the packaging or shipping of this item. I ordered it as a 2-pack with the black snail cream and they were both nestled happily in their boxes. I'm not sure what the difference is between this one and the black snail but since the price is good, i went with both. I think I will use this one for day and the other for night as the black snail cream gel goop is a touch thicker/more opaque.

This one I used right away this morning (after my shower, face wash, rosewater and rosehip seed oil, of course.) The jar is heavy, high-quality and looks really nice sitting on my bathroom counter. As for the gel...cream...stuff (it's a funky hybrid of all of these descriptors, really.) it's FAB. So far. (:

I have oily, acne-prone skin and many things can go wrong when using a new product. Usually, I can tell something might not be good for me right away but this seemed light and spread really nice while soaking in to a barely-sticky, satin finish. I don't feel like a snail crawled over my face, though when tapping it out of the jar it did feel kinda sticky and weird in a fun way. It's really easy to use too much. You just need to barely tap your (CLEAAAAN) finger into the stuff and then tap it around your face, then massage it in. Or you can use a beauty spatula or whatever to avoid touching the stuff in the jar but I'm not too finicky and I keep my hands pretty clean when doing my face up. I put on my makeup and stuff per usual and my makeup doesn't feel weird or like its sliding around. it feels better than normal, actually.

I occasionally have issues with surface dryness/scaliness so I will love to see how this stuff holds up to that but for my oily skin, its doing pretty well. Who know snail slime could be so cool? If it breaks me out like crazy or I turn into a giant snail, I will update at a later time!

column6: Crest 3D White Brilliance Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Deep Cleansing via Daily Two-Step System, 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
column13: Keep the polished look from the dentist at home.
column14:
Itâ€™s been years since Iâ€™ve whitened my teeth. While I love having white teeth, I hated the sensitivity caused by whiteners and worried it was eroding my enamel. Then BzzAgent sent me a new and more gentle product - Crest 3D White Brilliance Daily Cleansing Toothpaste and Whitening Gel System.

The product promises that it keeps your smile up to 99% as white as a professional polish with daily use 4 weeks after a dental cleaning. I like that this is incorporated in your normal brushing routine, no messy strips or trays. Just 1 minute per step twice a day!

The first toothpaste is a cleanser that deep cleans, while fighting cavities. It has a minty taste that I loved, but the gritty polish took awhile to get used to and if you're missing enamel could be abrasive. The second product is a gel that whitens and polishes teeth by removing surface stains. I felt a cooling sensation, but nothing that uncomfortable. After several days I didn't notice it at all. My teeth looked and felt clean for hours after brushing.

I had just happened to get a cleaning before I started using this product. I felt like after 3 weeks my teeth actually looked better than after the dentist. My teeth looked a shade whiter and just as shiny and bright. Don't expect a big change in whiteness. I was so pleased when my spouse noticed the change. And best of all, no sensitivity! My teeth and gums felt great.

column6: LOUISE MAELYS 14\ 35cm Short Straight Hair Bob Wig Anime Cosplay Costumes Pink"
column13: Grey Mix Black...Short Bob...has  subtle lavender/pink highlights mixed in
column14:
The Louise Maelys 14\\\ short, straight hair, bob wig, grey mix black. Is very nice quality. The fit can be adjusted using hooks just like more expensive wigs.
The wig is heavy compared to my expensive wigs, but the Louise Maelys wigs are meant to be used for costumes & Cosplay.

When I looked closely at the wig, I noticed highlighted areas of a soft lavender/pinkish color sprinkled throughout the silver gray wig. Individual strands of black hair are evenly mixed throughout the wig too. I really like the addition of the pinkish highlights.

The wig holds it shape nicely & is a little puffy at the back. It's a very flattering cut/shape. I was surprised how nice the wig looks on me. The color doesn't work for me, but I chose this for costume wear, not to flatter me.

As usual, the bangs are too long & will have to be trimmed. The wig has a nice sheen. In some lighting it is too shiny, but in natural light the shine looks like healthy, natural hair.

This style fits short in the back so you will have to pull your hair up, hold it with clips then use a wig cap. For me, using a wig cap always makes wearing wigs more comfortable. I put my hair in a low pony tail (sometimes two or three low ponytails so I don't have a huge bump at the back) then clip them up. Then I tuck everything, including wispy ends into a wig cap. The low ponytail/s help anchor the wig which prevents it from moving up the back of my head. Review sample provided.

Very nice costume wig."

column6: Oral Irrigator â€“ Portable, Dual-Speed Water Flosser â€“ Strong Water Stream Powered by 2 AA Batteries
column13: A great alternative to string floss.
column14:
With traditional flossing that involves the dreaded strings, I often find myself failing to get around to doing it and it is not enjoyable at all. My gums often bleed and I end up only flossing a couple of nights before the dentist visit. I have been wondering if there has been another way to get the benefits of flossing without the troublesome process, and I stumbled upon this water flosser.

Upon opening the package, it is relatively quick to assemble and it feels sturdy in the hand. It has a little bit of weight to it, but, in my opinion, that makes it more comfortable and easy to hold onto. The water tank has ridges along the sides to accommodate fingers and allows for a better grip, also. The water nozzle simply slides into place along the top. I like the fact that the battery compartment has a little slot to unlock it so you can be sure water does not leak in and the batteries are secured and won't fall out. The tank holds a good amount of water, but I end up going through two tanks. For some reason I over clean my teeth. I brush four minutes at a time, and I guess I floss them thoroughly, also. But that is okay. It is extremely easy to fill with water.

Another benefit is that it is so much faster to floss with this water flosser. I can have my teeth flossed in 2 minutes using the high setting, as compared to 5 minutes with string floss. The high setting gives enough penetrating power to get through the cracks of the teeth without damaging gums.

One thing I quickly learned with the irrigator is that you need to keep the nozzle in your mouth at all times with your mouth closed, and you need to spit out the water often to ensure the water stream is getting in between the teeth.

Overall, I am loving this device and I am glad that it has taken away my need to use string dental floss.

I received this product at a discount in exchange for an honest review.

column6: Merkur \1904\" Safety Razor 42C"
column13: Perfect for people with small hands! Retro without Reason!
column14:
I thought I'd go retro and try a double edge razor like I started with, 50 years ago. There is something cool about a double edge razor and I looked at cheaper and more expensive razors that this one. I also ordered a 100 pack of Derby blades with the razor along with a smaller pack of Feather blades. The Derby blades came with the razor, but the Feathers are on some slow boat from China and won't be here for another month or so.

The first thing I noticed about the Mekur was that the top does not open like my original Schick double edge... the handle screws off the bottom, the the head breaks into two pieces. This seems to require quite a bit of handling of a sharp razor blade just to put a new blade in each time... far less convenient than a butterfly top opening. The second thing I noticed in using the razor for the first time was how SHORT the handle is, compared with any other razor I've used. From the bottom of the handle to where your fingers will hit the business end of the razor is just 2 3/4 inches... that does not leave a lot of room for manipulating this razor across my ruggedly handsome mug.

But like any new thing, it is something that takes an adjustment period...after a week of using, I'm still noticing that it is a short handle, but not quite as bothersome.

The last thing I noticed is that the blade needs to be really screwed down in the head to effectively shave without becoming an involuntary blood donor. I didn't do that with the first shave and the blade managed to gouge that handsome epidural layer of my face a few times. My cheap blades are somewhat coloring this review, as they don't seem to be every effective in getting a great shave. I've never had a tough beard - a typical three or four blade cartridge lasts me weeks before I feel some sense of obligation to change it for a new one. But after about four shaves with the Derby double edge, I noticed that the double edge shave was missing quite a few spots, evenwith repeatedly going over certain areas. By 4pm, I looked like I hadn't shaved that morning. Perhaps the Feather blades - if they ever show up - will be better.

Summary - it's cool being retro, and it is more of a ritual to shave with a double edge razor. But it is not as clean a shave and I'm not sure I will stick with it. My Harry's razors are must faster, cleaner and frankly, safer.

column6: Brazilian Keratin Hair Treatment 300ml Professional Complex Blowout with Argan Oil Improved Formula and Fragrance Keratin Research Available Worldwide
column14:
I recently bought the Keratin Research Forte (which is good for 1a-3c curls). I have 3b hair which is thick, course, curly, and frizzy. I bought it on eBay because it was a little bit cheaper and free shipping. I think I paid about 28 dollars for a smaller bottle. My hair length is a little bit past my collarbone. It took me about five hours to do. My mom and sister helped me out in our bathroom. We had a floor fan going and the window open. My eyes burned a little bit, but it wasn't anything unbearable. It didn't even smell badly; it actually smelled like coconut.

I thought that it wouldn't work, to be honest. I watched the video on Keratin Research's website a few times. My hair just never looked -- I don't want to say saturated because you don't want it to be saturated -- but it just didn't have the same covered-in-solution look. My hair didn't really become any more manageable to blow dry or straighten either. Some people have noted that during the process, they saw and felt an immediate change in their hair texture. That didn't happen for me, so I had my reservations.

Anyway, I washed my hair around Day 3 or Day 4 with salon-quality products (be sure to avoid sulfates!), and I felt the silkiness in my hair right in the shower. While washing my hair, I noticed my hair was getting curly again. To be honest, I didn't expect it to straighten my hair. So when I am done washing my hair, I notice my hair isn't frizzing up, tangling, or doing any of the normal things it usually does. It was silky, soft, and I could run my fingers right through it. I even took a hairdryer to it on high heat, medium speed and ran my fingers through it for a little bit while it was wet for a minute or so. I have such loose and shiny waves now. I have only washed it once. Next time, I won't take a dryer to it to see how it turns out.

For 23 years, I have had unruly hair. I am the only jewish person in my town, so I am sick of standingout with my big, curly, nappy hair. It really is so manageable now.

column6: Honest Amish - Classic Beard Oil - 2oz
column14:
Honest Amish beard oil quite simply cannot be beat.

I've tried other beard oils and always come back to this stuff. The scent is fresh, clean, and manly...has some black licorice and root beer tones to it. Not at all overpowering, but it'll pleasantly stick with you for several hours. The oil itself feels great and really works wonders for the beard. We have very high humidity lately, and it totally bushes out my beard. This oil tames it, nourishes it, and helps the beard lay nicely. It's not at all oily or greasy if you get it on your skin either.

The price is comparable with other oils on the market, but comparatively speaking, most other brands only give you one ounce, where Honest Amish gives you two. TOTALLY WELL WORTH IT. And it's all natural and organic. Great for your face and doesn't seem to be an issue for sensitive skin. If you want your beard to look its best, buy this beard oil.

column14:
I have been using an eyelash curler for years! They have always pinched and
hurt when curling lashes. This eye lash curler from Fuchsia is great!! I
can't even tell if I am curling my lashes because there is absolutely no
pain or pinching. The only thing I would recommend is to have the top two
parts of curler a different color than black. I have dark lashes, so I
can't see if I have my lashes between curler or not because there is no
pain. But, when I check my lashes after curling, it is curling them closer to the lid
and I am not getting the crease in the lashes either. It is unreal!!
I have tried Maybelline, Revlon, and others. Revlon had been the best
for me before I purchased the Fuchsia Line, but it was never pain free.

column6: Aveeno Eczema Therapy
column14: This works like a miracle. I have face eczema one or twice a year for the past 3 years due to allergy, and it always disappear after a steroid shot and a week of prescription pills. This summer it came back again. I went to the hospital as usual and got a shot and a week of pills. But after that week, it came back again. It disappears for two days and reappear for 2 days for about a month, and suddenly it got worse that I could not stand it anymore. I went to the allergy clinic and got a blood test for allergy. They also scheduled an appointment for me to get skin tests to find out exactly what i am allergic too. But because of those tests, I could not take any allergy pills for at least 5 days and steroid shot/pills for 6 weeks. My face was so bad during this period that I decided to go online and do some research. I found this cream and the white vinegar and decided to give a try. After 12 hours of using them, my face was much better, and after 3 days I could not even see the eczema on my face. I will still get my skin tests for allergy, but I will continue using them until I feel safe to stop. A bonus is that my acne even gets better.

column6: PORE MEDIC PORE PURIFYING MASK
column13: Left my skin feeling fresh and super soft!
column14:
Just tried out this mask not ten minutes ago. I was a bit intimidated when I took it out of the package as it's kind of gooey and slimey.

I washed my face with my usual Philosophy one-step cleanser and then put this mask on my face. Getting the mask to fit just right took a few minutes but I got it to cover my entire face. (I'm Asian so I don't know if that matters, bone structure-wise)

Keep in mind this mask is like a piece of cloth that's pretty wet that you drape over your face. It's not what I was expecting. I was expecting something that would stick to my face more and, when drying, would tighten up like those Biore deep pore cleansing strips. No biggie tho, was still easy to apply.

I let the mask mingle with my face for twenty minutes then slowly peeled it off. My skin seemed to have a bit of a glow to it and it felt super soft as I was rubbing in the remainder of the serum.

Conclusion: I'd definitely buy this again.

I loved how it made my skin feel afterward and the scent of it is very light, tho I can't put my finger on what exactly it smells like.

I've uploaded a mugshot-like selfie of me with the mask on. Don't be scared! ;)

column14:
I have recently been introduced to the world of essential oils by friends and family and I've tried using a number of things at their suggestion, all of which I have found almost thrilling, like working magic through the process of highly concentrated liquids. I use essential oils in many tinctures and to scent my household. And while I make my own blends, I enjoy trying out other ones to discover what works best for me.

I've long been in need of something to inspire an energy boost and having experience with Plant Therapy brand oils, I wanted to try this. This particular blend of essential oil smells, according to my family (as I have no sense of smell), vibrant and refreshing, certainly a blend I need! Although I myself cannot smell, this is one of which I am able to catch whiffs and I can certainly feel it. It's powerful and invigorating and works wonderfully to energise as well as clear the sinuses in this time of allergies. The bottle is professional looking and the labeling is clear and informative. I am very happy with it and think it is a wonderful little blend.

column6: Seya Professional Rolling Cosmetic Makeup Case w/ 6 Trays
column14:
The outside of this case is very pretty with the shiny/matte silver contrast. It opens and closes smoothly and the smaller drawers slide out when it opens. All of the parts glide so there is no catching or having to force the case open or close. The handle is long enough for my to roll comfortably and I'm 5'8". I love the fact that it rolls because makeup can get very heavy. Plus it makes it easy to travel with. I can bring it in and out of the camper when we are traveling. It closes snuggly and locks are built in to the closing clasps. So no dangling locks.
It's not a huge case and would be easy to store in a closet or cabinet. But the compact size is no indication of the inside this case is extremely roomy and can fit a ton of makeup and other makeup supplies. It has a little weight to it but is overall lightweight and easy to carry/roll.
There dividers that can be moved so I can customize the case to my needs. If I need a small space the divider easily comes out and slides in a another pre-cut notch. If I don't want sections I can take the divider out completely. Whether the drawers are full or half full the makeup stays in place without falling or rolling around the case. I am confident that my makeup is safe even if the case should encounter rough travels. I also feel confident the outside of the case could withstand rough encounters. Although I am hoping that my case is always treated with love and care.
I received this product at a discount in exchange for my honest opinion but the opinion expressed is all my own.

I thought I found the perfect item in the Essential Wellness diffuser. Unfortunately, the scent is not emitted on a continual basis from beginning to end. So being efficient by purchasing a 300ml diffuser really didn't work with this product. I would look for either a smaller diffuser or another one that can process the oil/water on a continual basis.

column6: Brazilian Blowout Acai Daily Smoothing Serum 8oz/240ml
column13: Beware how much product you use!
column14: I have naturally straight hair, but it does get frizzy sometimes, I have lots of flyaways. In terms of smoothing my hair, it has done its' job, I do feel as if my hair is much more manageable throughout the day when I use this, than when I do not. This is a SERUM so you literally only need a PEA sized amount. I have a lot of very thick hair and a very oily scalp so any "heavy" product makes my hair feel greasy and gross. If I used more than a pea sized amount my hair would feel greasy and gross, but I use a pea sized amount every morning and it has been great. My hair does not feel heavy at all, but it does feel smooth and manageable. Even if you have a lot of hair, curly, straight, whatever, DO NOT go crazy on this. Start with a pea sized amount and go up if you feel as if you can. I know if I used more product my review would be extremely different. The product smells great and goes on smoothly, even my hands aren't greasy after I've used it because my hair absorbs it instantly. Overall I'm really glad that I bought this product, and I know that it will last for a very long time because it's so rich.

column14:
Tips for getting the most out of this moisturizer:

-Test on a small area of your skin first to check for any allergies.
-If you have sensitive skin or if you are using Retinol for the first time, start with using the moisturizer just twice or thrice a week (at night) to begin with, and then gradually increase to daily use.
-For best results, use it with your regular toner and serum. You can use a hyaluronic acid serum, vitamin c serum or even a retinol serum (if you are a seasoned retinol user).
-If you are in a colder region and your skin starts to dry, you can alternate with a more moisturizing cream.
-Wear sunscreen during the day.
-Regular long term use is the key to seeing great results. .

Because common results are noticeable around 6-8 weeks of daily use and I have just received this product I will update my review with my progress but I wanted to leave tips Body Merry provided to me of this Retinol Moisturizer Cream (that I requested to be provided for evaluation and review.)

column13: Lighter shade than I epxected from the pictures.  Better for a fair-skinned blonde.
column14:
Maybe it is the color setting on my computer's monitor or maybe it is just my perception of what blush color should look like in the package, but I completely ignored the fact that this is the lightest color blush in the collection and decided it looked like a good color for me. In the pictures, the two darker colors (Vibrant and Flushed) seemed as though they'd be clownishly dark even for someone like me who is a brunette with skin that tans easily and a lot of color in my face even in the winter.

In reality, this shade would be perfect for a light-skinned blonde. It is a lovely color, but it doesn't show up on my skin much at all. It feels very silky and, were it the right color for me, would look nice on my skin. There appears to be a slight sheen to it when it is on but I wouldn't call it shiny. I thought it applied nicely even on middle-aged skin.

I'm going to give this another try when my face hits midwinter paleness because it is a lovely color. As scary dark as Vibrant looks in the pictures, it is probably a better shade for me.

column6: SweatBlock Antiperspirant - Clinical Strength - Reduce Sweat up to 7-days per Use
column13: I'd like to start things off by saying that Sweat Block ...
column14:
I'd like to start things off by saying that Sweat Block really does work. I've struggled for a couple years now with excessive armpit sweat and this stuff has finally given me back the confidence to wear shirts that aren't dark colors. This is the first product that I've ever enjoyed enough to write a review for.

PROS:
1) Easy application - just put it on at night and let it dry.
2) Lasts for a long time - I usually get about 4-5 days per application
3) Greatly reduces armpit wetness, but doesn't completely prevent sweating, allowing your body to cool itself properly without getting pit stains

CONS:
1) Odd Smell - kind of pungent, but easily covered with a daily application of regular deodorant
2) Skin irritation - now, it doesn't irritate my skin much, but I have noticed some dryness/itching, especially right after it dries. People with sensitive skin might have bigger issues with this, so keep that in mind.
3) Doesn't meet 7 Day cycle as advertised

Overall, this is a great product with only a few small drawbacks to consider. If you struggle with excessive sweating, I highly recommend trying this. I'm not even halfway through my first box and already plan on ordering more soon.

BONUS TIP:
After my second application, I noticed that the wipe still had quite a bit of liquid in it and didn't feel completely used. So, I stuck it in a small zip-lock sandwich bag to keep it from drying out. For my next application, I reused the same wipe, and guess what, it still worked! And after that, the wipe finally felt used up. So essentially, you can get 2 uses per wipe, doubling the number of uses per box!

column14: People, if you haven't heard of the magic that is this product, let me enlighten you. I've used this product for almost 50 years. My mother and my grandmother used it, and they both had beautiful skin that never looked their age. My skin looks pretty good, too. It's the best thing to put on your skin since water. If you live in a dry climate, you'll love it. If you live in a humid climate, you'll love it. If you ever had a baby with diaper rash, you can't live without it. If you have eczema, or psoriasis, you'll reach for it every day. If your darling husband gets chaffed from damp drawers after basketball or golf, he'll thank you for sharing it with him. I can't tell you all the ways this product will make your life better because there isn't enough room here to do it. It's inexpensive, lasts forever, can be used on virtually every part of your body (because water flows through it and won't hold bacteria)...if I'm being thoughtless and run out, I literally panic until it's back in my hands. I gave my last tube to my daughter in law last week and was in a fine sweat until Amazon got me a new one. I wish I had a dollar for every person I've given a tube or jar of this to, and every person I've told to get this product, because I could have retired already. Seriously, there is NOTHING like this product for any amount of money on the market. When I was a girl, there were a lot of rumors about exactly where Mary Kay got the formula for this product--some old leather tanning guy, a healer lady who made her own ointments...doesn't matter. Here's what I know--get this product, use it for everything, and pat yourself on the back for doing so. You will wonder how you lived without it.

column6: SensatioNail Shield 3 in 1 Nail Protector, .72 Ounce
column13: these bad boys make removal a breeze
column14:
My main reason for buying these was to help protect my nails from the harsh reality known as removing a gel manicure. While it is true, these bad boys make removal a breeze, they rather defeat the purpose of the whole, UV/Gel thing. After painstakingly careful application, and even an extra long cure (I had hoped doing it longer the second time around would make the polish last better, nope.) the so called protection starts to peel immediately, and if they donâ€™t, they will after your first shower, even if it is over 24 hours later. (Revision: They will try and peel after not only a shower, but any use of hot/warm water, so good luck doing those dishes.)

As for the protection of the nail, again I am going to have to say these fail the test. While removing the traditional manicure left scratches and abrasions on my nails, I was rather shocked to find a crack down my thumbnail. From tip to cuticle. More than a little disconcerting.

Moral of the story, if you want easy removal, these are for you, but if you started using a gel cured UV manicure to help your stay prettier longer, I would stick to the traditional primer layer.

Which is to say. Iâ€™m not hating on the brand. So far I have loved every color and the long lasting polish, even if it does get a bit tricky to get off in the end. I would just stay away from these polish loosening nightmares. Thereâ€™s a chance I still havenâ€™t mastered the application process, but Iâ€™ve got to say, after two tries, it hasnâ€™t gotten any better.

column6: Panasonic ES-LV81-K Arc5 Menâ€™s Electric Razor, Wet/Dry with Multi-Flex Pivoting Head, High-Performance Motor, and included Premium Automatic Clean & Charge Station
column14: I purchased this razor because i have Rosacea and shaving irritates my skin.  The head has two degrees of motion that provides for a smoother shave.  I purchased the version with the automatic cleaning system because i thought that part of the problem i have shaving is my ability to get the razor clean enough.  It appears i was right, because using the razor with the automatic cleaning is producing a very good result while hand cleaning did not.  To be sure i always rinse the shaver out by hand before using the automatic cleaner - this removes hairs from the razor.  I also am careful to shave slowly, focusing on minimizing my discomfort and producing a result without bumps or cuts and minimal redness.  The result is the best shave i've had in years.  A friend believes that these razors always start off with a good result, but no matter what you do within a year or two even replacing the heads won't bring the shave back to the quality you had when you first used it.  That remains to be seen and i'll certainly update my review if i experience the razor going downhill in quality.  Why four stars instead of five?  Using the automatic cleaner isn't cheap.  Beyond the initial cost there is a cost for the soap/brush dispensers you have to change every month.  Also, the automatic cleaner is definitely noisy, and, there is no way to tell the razor NOT to charge so that you can ensure a longer life from the battery while still getting a good clean; its both or charging but not cleaning without charging - if you want to wait for it, you can set it to clean, dry and charge, then pull the razor out during the dry and place it on a something to dry by air.

column6: Vitabath Fresh Citrus Twist Bath And Shower Gels
column13: Vitabath Plus Went Down the Drain Too
column14:
The delicious fragrance of the original Vitabath Plus for Dry Skin is gone. It's been replaced by an unpleasant, chemical odor that lingers in the shower and on the skin. The gel is suspiciously thinner too, indicating that the advertised formula has been watered down, and consequently, it's likely less effective as a moisturizing agent. Even those who don't have dry skin should be concerned. If Vitabath is now using inferior ingredients, as signaled by the nasty smell and thin consistency, there may be cause for worry about where those ingredients come from.

The original fragrance made bathing a scrumptious pleasure for all the senses, enveloping the shower and the whole bathroom in a distinctive bouquet that was not too sweet, not too spicy, but just right. The Goldilocks of bath & shower gels, the original Vitabath Plus made you want to hang about and bask in scented bliss. The new Vitabath Plus makes you want to run for a chemical neutralizing agent. It would sure be interesting to discover who was in the focus group that gave Vitabath the go-ahead to reformulate their product into a thin, foul-smelling mockery of the orange-pink stuff we loved.

column6: Revlon RV544N6 Tourmaline 1875W Ionic Dryer
column13: Lackluster hair dryer that is a fire and safety hazard to boot!
column14:
Purchased this about a year ago based on the "#1 seller" designation and good price. I was disappointed in the performance pretty much immediately, as it seemed to lack the power of the dryer it was replacing. This doesn't matter as much for me, as I have a shorter hairstyle, but it did matter for my wife. Also, despite the dryer categorized as being Tourmaline Ionic Ceramic, which is supposed to use a type of heat that doesn't over dry your hair or create frizz/static, I felt like this product produced a dry type of heat that did just that. Therefore a few days ago I looked around Amazon and ordered a different brand that will hopefully perform better.

Now the bigger issue - The very next morning after ordering the new blowdryer, my wife was using this Revlon and was freaked out when it suddenly started sparking and smoking in her hand. And when I say sparking, I mean she said there were sparks showering out of the unit. Luckily she got the dryer unplugged, but not before it burned through half the cord. I was in there immediately after this incident and could smell the burned rubber. I set out to write a review and now see that many of the other negative reviews had the same scary situation with the dryer nearly exploding or catching fire during use. You would think that based on the frequency there would be a recall on this model. This dryer was an underachiever before it blew up, but now, with the safety hazard factor, I would urge anyone looking at this model to steer clear. There are plenty of other $20.00 hair dryers that do not carry a risk of injury or fire, so why take a risk?

column14:
This is my favorite Real Techniques brush. Like many others have said, it may be a little bit large to be used for blush, although I've used it that way in a pinch.

I use this as my primary powder brush for setting my foundation or finishing powder and even bronzer.

The tapered shape is not different from the shape of many higher end powder brushes, and it fits really well on different areas of the face. The side of the brush is quite functional as well if you want to sweep powder over a larger area.

It's nice and fluffy and the synthetic bristles are soft, which makes it an ideal brush for blending. I often contour on top of my foundation with a bronzer or contour powder, then I use setting powder or foundation powder to set the other areas of my face and to blend my contour out. column6: Double Edge Safety Razor
column13: Slippery weak handle, but gives a good shave
column14:
This razor's handle is slick when wet, and a little hard to hold. (Most likely ABS.) Coating the handle in hot glue will make it easier to hold and less frustrating when soapy. (Sugru or silicone will work. Standard glue not recommended.) It doesn't feel flimsy, but it's not durable: I flew with this razor in an outside pocket of my luggage, and the handle cracked. It also takes a little care to screw the head onto the body, because the threads don't line up easily, and this could lead to a ruined razor with stripped threads if you don't pay attention to what you're doing.

On the positive side, I like the shape/tolerances of the head. Blades fit well, and it's easier to get them centered properly than in my Mercur razor. The Edwin Jagger razor is also less aggressive: if I pass the razor down my cheek after the stubble is mostly gone, I often don't even feel the blade. The trade-offs are that it's more likely to clog, and it's not good for shaving other body parts.

column6: Neutrogena Healthy Skin Blush
column13: Powder is silky smooth - blush not blushy enough.
column14:
This came as three compacts, one of the Rosy blush#10, one of the nude-like powder Luminous #50 and one darker brick-like shade called Bronzed #40 They are all labeled as "blush" on the front of the compact, but they are not all blush.

Rosy: The Rosy is not rosy enough. It barely shows up on my pale pale skin. It looks rosy in the compact but it doesn't go on that deep on your cheeks. The powder just slides on, it's a lovely powder physically, it's smooth and easy to apply and has a faint luster to the powder. I would be tempted to get the the blush in a deeper shade like "Flushed". It doesn't come with a brush, so if you're going to take it with you to reapply, you'll have to carry a brush with it. I do like my blush to be the 8 hour kind, This isn't but I think I'd be ok with it if it actually showed up on my cheeks to start with.

Luminous: definitely NOT a blush, but does make a nice light all over foundation. That's how I've been using it. As someone else mentioned you can use it on your eyelids, as well. It's also silky smooth and looks beautiful as just something to smooth out your skin some and leave a slight shine to your skin. (not for covering heavy imperfections)

Bronzed: I've used it on my eyelids. It's not very dark, but still too dark to use as an all over finish and too light to use as a blush. I don't contour my face, so I can't speak to it's efficacy for that.

Overall - the Rosy is not rosy enough when applied, the compact is a little difficult to open, I have to slide my fingernail in between the lid and bottom at the corner to open it without fighting it. No brush means you can't just toss it in your purse. I think I'll try the Flushed, stay tuned for my review of that.

column6: Micro Touch Safety Razor Chrome
column13: Best Leg Shaver I've Ever Tried
column14:
I originally bought this razor at a local department store for my husband to use. He really likes Pawn Stars and I thought it would be cool. He tried it and did not care for it. He said it did not give him as smooth a shave as a regular multi-bladed razor. I was disappointed but decided to try it on my legs.

I approached the razor with some trepidation. You see, as a child, I had an accident with my mother's "safety razor." I nearly cut off one of my toes in an attempt to emulate my mother shaving. I still have the scar 45 years later. However, I tried to forget that and started shaving. After I was done I was amazed! This is possibly the closest smoothest shave I've ever had.

I've been using this razor for two months now and have noted an added benefit. My legs are usually full of scars and very itchy. So I get scars from shaving and from scratching. This has not happened with this razor. My legs look and feel healthy. I'm actually proud of my legs now.

Could I get the same result with another razor like it? Maybe. But I'm sticking with this one. Also, I love the little stand it comes with. Keeps the razor high and dry off the tub surface. I would recommend this razor to my friends if they want a close, smooth, and scar free shave.

column6: Oral-B Deep Sweep 1000 Electric Rechargeable Power Toothbrush
column13: I was disappointed that the product did NOT come with a travel ...
column14: This product definitely cleans teeth well but it QUITE strong.  It made my gums very sore after the first few uses and I had to stop using it for a few days, then alternate with manual brushing for a few days until now I can use it 2x/day without issue. There is NO way to adjust the intensity, one simple on/off button only. It is LOUD, really loud, especially compared to the sonicare I had previously - something to consider if you'll be using it near someone that's sleeping. I was disappointed that the product did NOT come with a travel cap for the brush like the sonicare does, so basically no way to keep the brush head clean/protected when traveling. I also find the brush head quite large as is the "stem" of the brush head. I wouldn't suggest this product for someone with a small mouth or trouble opening their jaw really wide.  I'm not sure if it is the design of the brush, but the charging base seems to accumulate a lot of grime, even with rinsing the brush head under water while running post-brushing. The brush head pops off easily for cleaning thankfully but I've been surprised how messy the base was with only 1-2 weeks of use. Good clean but not recommended for people who need a more gentle brush (look at sonicare), really should come with travel cap, and could be quieter.

Needless to say HPM will now be a permanent part of my oral hygiene routine.

Four stars because the unit was blissfully easy to set up & operate and very quiet for the most part. I say most part because the unit had a very faint squeaking sound after a couple hours of operation, but I want to wait and run it a few more times before revising my review. Love the timer & light options, the EO blend I put into the water came out strong & filled my office but didn't encroach into my colleagues spaces or the adjacent hallway. Am taking it home to see how it fares in a larger room. I have signed up for the 1 year warranty and am curious to see what being a VIP (no extra cost for either) will include. Stay tuned!

column6: Panasonic Dental Water Flosser
column13: It IS easier to handle and clean - you only have a small tank compared to a large one with the Waterpik and it's easy to charge
column14: I previously have used a Waterpik flosser with the tank and I wanted something a little less clunky and easier to clean, so I went with this model. It IS easier to handle and clean - you only have a small tank compared to a large one with the Waterpik and it's easy to charge. But when the instructions tell you to put the nozzle into your mouth - you really want to do that. I first turned it on expecting it to work similarly to my Waterpik flosser and it sprayed out all over the bathroom. Even across the entire room!! It has 3 settings - jet, air regular and air soft. The pressure comes out with such force that the only setting I can use it on is the air soft which is actually meant to "massage your gums". I am afraid if I tried any other setting, I wouldnt have any gums left! That being said, the lowest setting still seemed to do a decent job of flushing particles out from my teeth and gums, so I will continue to use it and just be careful to start it up in my mouth and keep it there until I turn it off!!

column13: Everyone on the planet needs to run for their life to buy this
column14:
I bought this on ebay, as it was cheaper there (2.99). But this is the best thing I have ever used in my life. If you have eczema, or dry skin, or icthyosis, this is the absolute best thing you can use. I soaked in the tub for like 20 minutes then took the area I was rubbing out of the water or stood up. When I got too dry I sat back in the tub. Another hour and a half later, so much dirt came off in the tub and my skin glowed.
(Note that I have done this kind of routine before using a regular sponge (and soap) and dead skin NEVER came off! Not only that but my skin continued to have a lot of problems. It got better when I stopped using soap, but it was still there.)

After I finished, dry areas where I had scars from eczema flair ups visibly faded, cracked skin visibly reduced. I am very sure that at the most by the end of the month the cracks in my skin will be completely gone. My skin will finally be clear for the first time since I was a kid. I have catching up to do.

I didn't use any soap except some bubble bath, and epsom salt i poured in the water. For moisturizer, I just took a quick shower to wash my hair and rinse off, and then while my skin was wet put raw cocoa butter.

Yes the towel did shrink, but It didn't stop me from using it, my hand still went in. I might try what that other commenter said about putting a face towel inside it and using it like a sponge.

I am 100% sure using this towel is the only way to get legitimately clean, especially if your skin seems to be abnormally dry. This product should have a 5 star rating, and everyone on the planet should be running for their lives to use this, especially if you have any form of dry skin. This will cure it. Lotions did not work for me, regular soaps made my skin way worse, moisturizing soaps only slowed the issue, sugar/salt scrubs gave me scars and discoloration, alpha hydroxy lotion did nothing. I can not emphasize enough. If you have icthyosis oreczema, dry cracked skin-- use this.

column6: Derma Sea The Ultimate Face Kit, Complete Dead Sea Face Care Kit for Immediate & Long Term Results Facelift Cream with Hyaluronic Acid, Vitamin C Serum & Eye Lift Cream for Dark Circles
column13: Best balance of immediate and long-term effects I've seen
column14:
How do you compare the hundreds of skin care products? As a regular tester, I've arrived at a list of key considerations. I hope these are helpful to you!

~ Fragrance: Very mild, faintly floral/herbal.
~ Feel during application: All three of these are light, white lotions. They go on smoothly and absorb quickly.
~ Feel after absorption: Smooth, moisturized without being oily or damp. The skin conditioners in this set do an excellent job adding smoothness without leaving a film. I canâ€™t feel it on my face unless I touch it, no heavy feeling.
~ Is it best for a certain skin type?: Probably fine for all. It works on my sensitive, oily skin. Very dry skin will probably require an additional, heavier moisturizer.
~ Is it tested on animals?: No.
~ Packaging: Lovely, upscale-feeling cardboard display box which opens to reveal three tubes. Each is a 15g/0.52 oz plastic squeeze tube with a screw-off cap and a fine point dispenser. The way this set is packaged really adds to the luxury/spa/treat feeling of using it.
~ Immediate cosmetic effects:* My redness and uneven skin tone is immediately calmed and redness reduced. Not in an â€œOMG this totally turned my skin normalâ€ sort of way, but in a â€œwow, my face looks betterâ€ sort of way. My skin looks soft, firm, and healthy after use. I have to say as a semi-professional product tester, not much of what I test ends up getting used on my face daily (not because the products are bad, but because there is only so much I can put on one area of skin in one day!). Most get used on my neck, hands, arms etc. This is one of the rare ones I will continue to use on my face because I like the way it leaves my skin looking and feeling.
~ Potential long-term effectiveness:* Okay ....there are some overhyped ingredients in here. Pearls and caviar sound classy and have some benefits to the skin, but nothing to write home about. Dead sea minerals are definitely good for the skin. There are a large number of better active ingredients in this set including vitamin C, hyaluronic acid, retinyl palmitate, vitamin A, allantoin, algae extracts, peptides, azelaic acid (which may help treat rosacea), licorice, and Dimethyl MEA. This is actually an excellent anti-aging and anti-inflammatory formula. If you have reddened or sensitive skin, definitely give this a try.

Other notes - One critique I have of the set is that the tubes you use on your whole face are the same size as the tube intended for eyes. So, youâ€™ll run out of the face tubes before using up the eye tube. One thing I do appreciate is that this is an Israeli product. Like buying made in the US products, I like to support industry in Israel.

*Know the difference between cosmetic and long-term effects: Cosmetic effects are immediate and only present when the product has been applied recently - just like makeup. Long-term effects take longer to see and should remain when you stop using the product (but don't when you find something effective - your skin needs continuing support). The ideal product would be both cosmetically and long-term effective, but it's more realistic to expect a formula to tilt towards one or the other. This set is actually one of the best I've ever seen for providing both short and long-term effects.

column13: I'm pretty happy with this product
column14: I will update when I have more results, but thus far, I'm pretty happy with this product. I'm more concerned about my eyebrows rather than my lashes, but I'm using it on both anyway. I did extensive googling on the ingredients before using this, and I was pleasantly surprised. After reading some horror stories about women who used different products on their hair to aid with growth, I was a bit concerned, but laboratory testing on the ingredients in this didn't turn up anything negative. column14: I did not buy this product, someone had bought it, used it, didn't like it, and gave it to me.  I have very dry hair and and even drier scalp.  I used it as a rinse-out conditioner the first time I used it, and then the 2nd time I tried it as a leave-in conditioner, following the directions on the jar.  It kind of worked on my hair and scalp.  My hair and scalp were both not as dry, but still nowhere near "normall".  While I did not find the smell of the product offensive, my husband was not pleased with the smell.  Then I decided to try applying the conditioner before I washed my hair, leaving the product in my hair for about an hour before shampooing.  After, my ends finally felt soft and my scalp was not one big dry, itchy flake.  I then used the product as a pre-shampoo conditioner on my 8 year old daughter, who inherited her father's middle-eastern thick, coarse, dry hair.  Her hair came out soft and less-tangle prone.  If you have this product, don't give up right away if it doesn't work on your hair, you may need to try different application methods before you find what works for your hair and scalp type.

column6: Philips Norelco 7700 Shaver
column14:
Iâ€™ve been a razor blade shaver for some 50 years. About every 5 â€“ 10 years I have the notion to try electric shavers. Part of my rationalization is that the technology has improved and the experience will be better than my last try. What I tend to forget is that the technology with razors has also improved. And of course the second part of the equation is â€œold habits die hardâ€.

When I saw the Philips Norelco Shaver 7700 for Sensitive Skin was available, I thought Iâ€™d give it a try. Of course I was hoping that this would be the magic time when I would be able to throw away the razor and the shaving cream and rely sole on an electric shaver.

I will be quick to admit that this is by far the best electric shaver I have tried. However, it takes some time getting used to â€“ the instructions say it takes 21 days going from razor to electric and those first few days are a bit rough. You can get rid of the shaving cream but as far as I am concerned, you will need to replace it with some skin conditioner. Shaving dry or with just water is not advisable â€“ I found it uncomfortable.

The Norelco shaver is quiet and fits in your hand very comfortable. If is well designed and does an okay job of getting a close shave. I still do not think it compares to a razor shave.

It looks nice and is easy to clean. If you are a committed electric shaver, then this might be a great option. If you have been using a razor for a long, long time, then you are probably going to find the shift a bit difficult.

column6: Mavala Switzerland Mavala Stop Nail Biting
column14: My boy had been sucking his fingers since he was in the womb.  He sucked them ALL THE TIME!  At 2.5 years old the roof of his mouth was becoming deformed and two of his teeth were not coming in.  We were very stressed out over this and really wanted him to stop but didn't want to go about it the wrong way and cause an even bigger dependency on it.  We tried the finger guard first, I had the wrist wrap so tight it left marks on my son's skin and he still figured out how to get his fingers out.  We tried positive reinforcement, and so many other approaches we read about online and nothing worked. I was VERY nervous about trying this product because so many reviews said that it made their child vomit.  I thought, how horrible!  After feeling like we had no other options, we finally tried this product.  I wish I would have used this first!!!!  It was SO EASY.  I let my son watch me put clear polish on my nails two days in a row.  On day 3 I asked him if he wanted me to do his nails.  Of course he said yes.  I applied this product to the nails of the two fingers that he sucks.  It dries really fast.  The first day he put his fingers in his mouth repeatedly and pulled them right back out.  He said he had stink on his fingers and we needed to wash his hands.  We washed them and then he tried it again.  We did this 3 times.  It did make him cough and he said he didn't feel good but he never vomited.  We told him he may be getting too old for his fingers  to taste good.  Mommy and Daddy don't suck our fingers because they don't taste good anymore.  He seemed to think this was pretty cool.  He was a big boy now!  The second day was about a 70% improvement and by day 3 he didn't even attempt to put his fingers in his mouth anymore.  It has now been 4 months and he hasn't attempted to do it since day 2. The roof of his mouth is correcting itself and his two teeth have come in and are almost lined up with the other teeth.  We are so thankful for this product!!!!!!

column13: Yes the color is nice, but application is a bit tricky
column14: I have to say I was suprised by this little liquid liner. I've been searching for one that is dark and a flat black. This definately fits the bill. It's long lasting when using a primer (I use wet and wild fregie's plain eye primer). Lasted all day and well into the night. It does seem to clump or flake when being taken off, but doesn't leave you with raccoon eyes. The reason I gave it 4 stars is the tip. Yes the color is nice, but application is a bit tricky. The give on the pointed end of the tip compared to the rest of the tip makes application a bit skippy. Getting a nice smooth line would take someone with lots of liquid liner experience to get right. This is NOT for a beginner. I have been applying liquid liners for some time and it still took me a few tries. The tip is a bit too hard it be feasible to get a perfect line without some issues, but over all I love it.
