column6: Waterpik Aquarius Water Flosser
column13: Your How-To Guide to This Does-It-All Water Flosser (and select Waterpik Models Comparison)
column14:
ASTONISHING (to me, anyway) HEALTH UPDATE (2/19/2017): WATERPIKING SAVES LIVES, MAYBE YOURS! REALLY! I MEAN IT! (I know, it sounds crazy...)

I finally broke down and got a Waterpik when my dentist told me I had periodontal pockets and would need a deep cleaning. I read somewhere that with regular use of a Waterpik, I might just be able to reverse those pockets and eliminate that need for an uncomfortable deep cleaning. I gave it a three-month try and it worked! No deep cleaning needed!

Also, I spoke with my primary care physician about plaque, and learned that there are two more (one of them could save your life) benefits to Waterpiking regularly. See my UPDATE at the end of this review.

I have noticed that others have asked a lot of the questions that I had early on inside of their reviews and in the customer questions section. So I thought I would gather up all of the answers and put them in one review. I hope this will be your Guide to Using Your New Aquarius Waterpik.

If you do find this review helpful, please click "Yes" below, I'd appreciate it!

HOW DO I AVOID MAKING MY GUMS BLEED WHEN I START USING MY WATERPIK?

It is not in the instructions anymore, but according to my husband, Waterpik used always to tell users to start by using the lowest "1" pressure setting and then to turn the pressure up one notch per day to get your gums adjusted to the Waterpik's pressure gradually. If you do this, you should be on "10", or whatever setting you prefer, in no time and with no gum bleeding.

HOW DO I KEEP FROM SPLASHING WATER EVERYWHERE?

There are two simple tricks never to see a water splash again. First, don't turn the Waterpik on until it is in your mouth. Second, keep your mouth closed except a slight parting of your lips to allow water to drain out of your mouth, while you use your Waterpik. That should take care of it!

THE ON/OFF SWITCH ON THE HANDLE IS HARD TO USE.

You will, unfortunately, just have to get the hang of how to master that switch. It seems to be a matter to where you apply pressure on the switch. It seems to work best when you apply pressure close to the center, rather than from the bottom or the top, in my limited experience. However, in the meantime, if you get frustrated, just use the on/off button on the face of the machine as a shortcut.

WHY DO THEY SEND SEVEN TIPS BUT ONLY PROVIDE SLOTS FOR TWO?

First of all, you only receive four different types of tips. The total number of tips adds up to seven because Waterpik provides three identical Classic Jet Tips (see below for descriptions of each). Most people choose only one style of tip for daily use (possibly two if you have periodontal pockets). The second slot can also be used for a partner or house-guest.

WHAT IS THE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN THE FOUR STYLES OF TIPS INCLUDED?

"CLASSIC JET TIP" (you get 3)
To identify it: it is the only tip style that you get three of.
Classic Jet Tips are for general use and replace flossing for people without crowns or other more-serious-than-fillings dental work. (For people with that sort of dental work, use the "Plaque Seeker Tip", described below.) Use the Classic Jet Tip unless you have a special reason to choose one of the others.
Rather than include links to the replacement tips in this review, I recommend that you just do a search for "Waterpik JT-100E". That way, there's no risk that this review will be filled with dead links.

If you search by the tip's name, you will probably get results that include tips that are not compatible with your Aquarius. So I have provided the actual model numbers of each tip so that you can search for the right one. If any tip that you want is not available on Amazon, you can buy it directly from Waterpik dot com. (Note For Ultra Buyers: the Ultra uses the same modeltips as the Aquarius, provided here.)

"TOOTHBRUSH TIP" (quantity: 1, but that is plenty for most)
To identify it: it looks like a tiny toothbrush.
This tip allows you to brush your teeth and Waterpik at the same time. As efficient as that sounds, there must be a reason why they included 3 Classic Jet Tips and only 1 Toothbrush Tip. I am guessing the reason is that this Brush Tip looks more efficient than it is -- especially if you have an effective toothbrush like a Sonicare.
Search for "Waterpik TB-100E" to find compatible replacement tips.

"PLAQUE SEEKER TIP" (quantity: 1) (my daily use tip)
To identify it: look for fewer bristles than are on the Toothbrush Tip.
The Plaque Seeker Tip is designed for use with crown, implants, and bridges, as well as for general use. So if you have any dental work more serious than fillings in your mouth (i.e. are you over 30?), you can just use this tip as your daily tip all around your mouth. "Removes bacteria and debris from hard to reach areas around dental restorations."
Search for "Waterpik PS-100E" to buy refills.

"PIK POCKET TIP" (quantity: 1)
To identify it: it looks like the Classic Jet Tip but with an extra pointy attachment at the end.
This one is for people who have periodontal pockets or furcations. It can "deliver medicaments" except that neither the Aquarius nor the Ultra is designed for that (they don't have "Medicament Reservoirs"), or just rinse deep below the gumline. Few people will choose to use the Pik Pocket as their daily tip. You would use this before or after you do your primary Waterpik rinse, and probably just on the areas that need it. This tip is supposed to be used only with the machine set to a pressure of "1", so don't forget to turn the pressure down before using it.
Search for "PP-100E" to get compatible replacement tips.

OTHER WATERPIK TIPS YOU CAN BUY ON AMAZON COMPATIBLE WITH THE WATERPIK AQUARIUS: these don't come with your Aquarius but they are compatible with it, and you may find them useful:
--Orthodontic tip OD-100E
--Tongue Cleaner TC-100E

Finally, Waterpik also offers a storage case that comes with six compatible tips. Search for TS-100E.

THE WATERPIK AQUARIUS VERUS THE WATERPIK ULTRA: A SHOWDOWN

Some reviewers have argued that the older [[ASIN:B00CU9VF2Q Waterpik WP100W Ultra Dental Water Flosser]] is a better device. However, many reviewers have claimed the opposite. Waterpik continues to make both. Here are the differences according to Amazon and Waterpik (you can do comparisons between any current models on Waterpik's website, just type in Waterpik dot com then choose Oral Hygiene):

This Model, the Waterpik Aquarius WP-660 is called the "Aquarius Professional" on Waterpik's site. That's cool, right?

As of this writing, the Ultra has fewer than 300 reviews that average 4.5 stars; this Aquarius has over 6,000 reviews that average 4.4 stars. Since I don't know if the Ultra's average rating is 4.500000 and the Aquarius's is 4.4999999999, I don't really see any difference in those reviews other than than a LOT more people choose to buy this Aquarius.

Differences Between this Aquarius and the [[ASIN:B00CU9VF2Q Ultra]]
--while on Amazon, prices vary, Waterpik thinks the Aquarius is the nicer machine because they charge $20 more for the Aquarius than for the Ultra;
--the Ultra has a button on the handle that you must hold down in order to keep the water flowing, if you let go, it stops; the Aquarius has an on/off toggle switch so that once you toggle it on, it keeps flowing without finger pressure, until you toggle it off;
--the Aquarius comes with three Classic Jet tips, versus two with the Ultra
--the Aquarius includes a massage mode (have to admit that I don't use this at all)
--the Aquarius includes an LED Function Indicator (ehh)
--the Aquarius includes a Timer/Pacer (I use this every day and know that I would stop sooner than I should if it weren't on there)
--the Ultra doesn't include anything that the Aquarius does not

Features That Are Identical Between the Aquarius and the Ultra
--both come in black and white (Aquarius, this page; [[ASIN:B00CU9VF2Q Waterpik Ultra White and Black available here]];
--same water pressure
--same flow rate
--same pulse rate
--both have 10 pressure settings
--the tips rotate 360 degrees
--water capacity both in volume and in seconds
--both have covered water reservoirs
--almost identical weight: 1.46 pounds for this Aquarius and 1.48 for the Ultra
--both have three-year warranties
--both only have plugs for North America

SOME OTHER MODELS AVAILABLE:

Waterpik Complete Care is still available for $10 more and gives you a shorter warranty (2 years instead of 3), no massage mode, no LED indicators, and fewer tips. Thumbs down.

If you're really price sensitive OR if you want to use medicaments OR you really hate filling the reservoir, the Waterpik Classic Pro is $30 less expensive on the Waterpik site (on Amazon, prices vary) includes a medicament reservoir, and holds up to 35 ounces (Aquarius and Ultra hold 22 ounces) but you will not get:
--the good reviews that the Aquarius and Ultra have; Classic Pro is not nearly as well-liked;
--the option of a black-colored model;
--the maximum water pressure of 100 PSI (it's 90 PSI instead)
--four pressure settings: you get only six pressure settings instead of ten (but honestly, how many people need the subtlety of more than six settings?);
--the super-important-to-me Timer/Pacer
--water control on the handle (it works like the Ultra: you have to hold a button down);
--a covered reservoir;
--covered tip storage;
--massage mode;
--LED Function Indicator;
--the ability to use any tips other than the Classic, the Pik Pocket and the Tongue Cleaner (Waterpik does not make compatible Orthodontic tips, Plaque Seeker tips, or Toothbrush tips for the Waterpik Classic Pro)
--the third year of warranty, Classic only comes with a tow-year warranty.

I hope this review has been helpful to you. Please feel free to leave comments, as you can see, I have responded to the only question asked, and am happy to answer more. And I'd very much appreciate a "Yes" click if you did find this review at all helpful. (I have dreams of one day qualifying for the VINE reviewer program...)

IMPORTANT HEALTH UPDATES (2/19/2017): WATERPIKING SAVES LIVES, MAYBE YOURS!

THE LIFESAVING UPDATE: My Primary Care Physician just informed me that PLAQUE in the MOUTH CAUSES PLAQUE in the ARTERIES AND VEINS! !! ! !! That was a big surprise to me. Now I'm REALLY going to use this baby twice a day (like I told my dental hygienist I do <w>).

A DENTAL HYGIENE BEST-PRACTICES UPDATE: My Primary also told me that using flossing brushes (like the Pixters my dentist told me to use) actually transfers bacteria from the first tooth to the second, and from the first and second to the third, and so on. Unless of course you use a new one for each tooth, each time. IMHO, they're way too expensive for that! column6: Sandalwood, 100% Pure Essential Oil - Best for Sleep Aid, Libido and Skin Enhancer-15 ml
column13: Smells like something that came out of a rain forest dwelling monkey
column14:
I'll preface this review with the fact that I have a highly sensitive nose. I usually detect developing smells in the environment minutes before anyone else in the room is able to. It's more of a curse than a blessing, because as a result, I can only deal with a small set of relatively pure (and unfortunately expensive) fragrances in my life. Most things that are not natural or "pure" smell "industrial" to me and will often lead to headaches and nausea in all but the smallest quantities.

So then...

After reading the glowing reviews, I decided to pony up the $50+ for this oil. I diffused it using a fairly high end, cold air atomizer. No water or additional carrier substances or blending oils were used.

The various descriptions refer to this scent as "warm" and "sensual". I found it to be neither of those. To me it was pungent and even, to my nose, rancid. It literally felt like it was stinging my nostrils and then punching me in the frontal lobe of my brain. Needless to say, it was unusable to me.

I'm not sure if it changed composition due to traveling in the mail during the summer or if it's just this bad off of the production line. This is the first product I've tried from this manufacturer, so it's hard for me to say.

After recovering from the initial assault to my senses, I attempted to blend minute quantities of this product with various light floral oils. It just got worse and worse. You know that smell when you mix fruity room sprays with some unholy bathroom or kitchen odor? Yeah, it was kind of like that.

I had to return this one and can't currently recommend it. Perhaps I'll try another bottle in the Winter. Then again, maybe not.

column6: Detangling Brush - Glide Thru Detangler Hair Comb or Brush - No More Tangle - Adults & Kids - Pink
column13: Turned Mornings Filled With Shrieks & Screams Into Silence
column14:
I have thick and wavy hair for a guy. My wife has thick and curly hair for a woman. Thus, my daughter was unfortunately cursed with hair that -- although beautiful -- is a real challenge to comb, style, wash, etc without making her scream and cry from all of the tangles and snarls. So, I have tried a few different products, and so far, I am most impressed with this one.

My Typical Morning: Wake-up, go potty, brush teeth, wake-up daughter (4 years old), feed dog, get dressed, wake-up daughter again, prepare my lunch, wake-up daughter a third time, get items ready for breakfast, and check on daughter who is typically finishing brushing her teeth. Then, I grab the brush, sit down on the toilet seat in the bathroom, and see my daughter's face sink. She tries to sneak past me, but I grab her. After some initial resistance, I am able to start brushing her hair. Then the whining and the squealing commences. Banshee-like shrieks, over-dramatic tears, etc. You all know what I mean...

Typically by the end, I have a head ache, I'm annoyed, and she is dramatically complaining about how much it hurt. So, thank you Detangling Brush for making my mornings a lot more manageable. The squealing and shrieking has definitely been moved to a minimum, and she doesn't try and run by me every morning now. I will say that it works really well.

So why the 4 stars? Well, I am not a fan of the handle area. I find that it isn't 'gripy' enough when using either in a dry environment, or a wet environment. The shape is a little awkward as well. I would prefer a nice contoured handle, or some sort of tactile grip on it.

Cost: For the cost, I am very pleased, but would be willing to pay a little more for a better handle.

Overall: This has made my life better and my daughter's life better. Great product, I fully recommend

column6: Color Oops Hair Color Remover Extra Strength 1 Each
column14: I have been coloring my own hair at home for about 12 years. I mean marathon coloring. I've had every color under the sun except for platinum. Over the last 2-3 years I like to think my taste in color has somewhat matured. I generally stick to rich dark browns and red browns (barring the brief fire engine red phase). I got home yesterday from a beach vacation and decided to refresh my color after my several days in the sun, saltwater, and chlorine. As usual, I opted for a rich reddish brown. Unfortunately, I used a new brand of color and to my horror, my hair was almost black even after blow drying. Being a seasoned veteran of the hair catastrophe clan, I rushed out to get some Color Oops. My hair isn't particularly long but it's ridiculously thick so I bought two boxes at Walmart for about $9-$10 each. I came home and followed the instructions to a T. (OK, so maybe I didn't quite hit the exact goals on the rinsing time. But I still rinsed like crazy!) I was left with this super awesome (read awful) brassy orange color. I was not shocked, I knew what to expect. But at least now I had a lighter color to work with. As soon as it was dry, I followed it with my regular brand of dark reddish brown. And this is the tricky part. I know from previous experience how quickly your hair will darken when recoloring after Color Oops. I've never applied color to my hair faster than I did today. And literally as soon as I stepped away from the mirror where I applied the color, I stepped to the faucet to rinse it out. Due to my haste, I do think I missed a few spots here and there but overall I was left with a color similar to my original goal color. I do feel like the final color is not quite as vibrant as I'd like. Call it "ashy" if you will. However, if you actually read the instructions, this is to be expected. Bottom line, I'm left with a color very similar to what I wanted originally and in time I'll be able to color it again to get exactly what I want. Much better than the black that I ended up with after the first round of color! Therefore, the Color Oops did exactly what it was supposed to do and for that I'm grateful. Again, for me, the biggest concern is making sure that you don't leave the 2nd round of color on too long or you'll end up right back where you started. Thank you Color Oops for another saved hair botch. Until next time....

column13: Man, is this one sharp razor
column14: Based on great reviews I got the Feather Razor Artist Club SS without ever using a straight razor, only using a double-edge razor before. In short, I cut my cheek pretty bad on my first attempt that will probably leave a one-inch scar. This was completely my fault, and NOT the razor's, because I tried to shave the opposite side of my face with my dominant hand instead of switching hands, like you're supposed to. As for the razor itself, it is very nice and well built, lightweight, and has a great, grippy handle. On a side note, I was surprised how small this razor is in person.  I've used the Feather Razor a few times now and it's definitely taking some getting used to. I have to go extremely slow because the blades I bought, the Feather Professional, are the sharpest blades I've come across in my lifetime and are pretty scary to use, and I'm learning which shaving angles work well without getting into my skin. Just like anything else, it just takes practice, I am definitely glad I bought it and absolutely recommend it, but learn from my mistake and prepare yourself beforehand, and know what you're doing before using it.

column6: Crest Pro-Health HD Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Healthier Mouth via Daily Two-Step System - 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
column13: Mouth feels clean, but Whitestrips whiten better
column14: Crest Pro Health HD comes with two tubes that are marked Step 1 and Step 2.  The tubes are also different colors (silver and blue) so you don't mix them up, which is a nice touch.  Step 1, the "Purifying Cleanser," is the larger, silver tube, and it's like a regular toothpaste.  It's nice and minty and a slightly aqua or blue color like some mint gel toothpastes are.  You brush your teeth with this first for 1 minute, and spit but do not rinse with water.  Step 2, the "Perfecting Gel," is in a smaller, blue tube.  It's a clear, somewhat runny or watery gel.  You brush with this second step for 1 minute, spit (but don't rinse), and brush for 1 minute more.  This gel tastes more like a product from the dentist's office.  It's not bad per se, but not nice and minty like regular toothpaste.  More of a medicinal taste, which is kind of unfortunate since it's the last taste you have in your mouth as Step 2.  One thing I liked about these products is that you feel more inclined to brush for longer; they recommend 3 minutes total of brushing (1 for the cleansing, and 2 for the purifying gel).  My mouth felt really clean afterwards.  The tubes are small, though.  My husband and I usually share 1 tube of toothpaste in the master bathroom, and I feel like this would be gone very quickly if two people used it.  I have used the Crest Whitestrips product in the past.  In my experience, those strips whitened my teeth faster and more noticeably.  This Pro Health HD product seems to me better at reducing stains or maintaining whiteness than whitening itself.  I didn't see any dramatic improvement, but my mouth feels clean. I got a free sample of the product from Crest.

column6: Degree MotionSense Dry Spray Antiperspirant, Shower Clean 3.8 oz
column14:
I normally use Degree Motion Sense stick but I thought I would try the Shower Clean Dry Spray.

Some of the product descriptions are definitely right. It does go on clean and there is no residue on your clothes; even my nice black work dress. The smell is pleasant and it lasts a while.

I wore this during days that were highs in low 90's and lows in high 60's with humidity that hovered between 70-90%. I am working an office job 9-5, but I am fairly active. My pedometer logs about 8 miles a day and I go to the gym 5 days out of the week.

I do not enjoy putting it on in a closed space like a bathroom. You definitely breathe in the fumes which is fairly unpleasant. By about 6pm, I start to notice that the feeling it faded; I am still protected from smell, but my armpit begins to feel more sticky which is so unpleasant in this humidity. I ran a 5k with this deodorant and applied some before hand, it lasted through the run just fine.

Overall, its a fine product. With the fact that the stick lasts long (on my arm pits and for the tube) its a better bang for your buck in my opinion.

column13: Great Product to Help Prevent/Treat Scarring
column14:
I purchased this lotion a few months ago to prevent a burn mark on my chest from scarring. After using this product almost every night for five months, I feel as though I can finally write an honest and thorough review.

Let me start by saying that I have sensitive skin that is very prone to scarring. However, it's been five months since I started using Alohi cream and the burn mark is completely faded! This is a big deal for me since in the past I've tried pure Vitamin E oil, Cocoa Butter, Shea Butter, you name it. None of those products were able to do what this Alohi cream did. This cream is now my go-to product to prevent scars.

As for the quality and experience with the product, itself, I found that the cream has a very pleasant, light, almost citrusy scent that I prefer over other creams that claim to prevent scarring or treat existing scars such as Cocoa or Shea butters. This makes sense because there is Orange Oil in the cream. It's not at all a strong scent, but you definitely pick up on it. The Alohi cream is thick but does not feel greasy or sticky at all. It absorbs into skin quickly, immediately leaving my skin feeling soft and moisturized. Another bonus is that it does not stain- the cream is white and it does not leave oil or grease spots on clothes or sheets.

Overall, I cannot say enough good things about this product. I definitely recommend it to anyone out there looking for a product to treat their existing scars or to prevent future ones! :)

column6: PIXNOR P2016 Portable 7-in-1 Facial and Body Ultra Brush for Women & Men - Deeply Cleaning Skin - Natural Anti-aging - Microdermabrasion Cleanser Tool Set - Exfoliating Dead Skin Cells - Stimulate Collagen - Beauty Care Massager Facial Massager Cleaner
column13: Not worth the money for the number of useful parts
column14:
PIXNOR P2016 Facial Brush 7 in 1 Facial Massager Face Brush with 7 brush heads Rosy

This facial massager comes with 7 different massager heads and runs off of 2 AA batteries. The handle portion of the massager is not waterproof so I would recommend removing the brushes and exfoliating heads before cleaning with water.

I found it to be very underpowered. Though there are two speeds, I would classify them as slow and slower. Any pressure of the brush heads onto the skin causes the motor to slow down even more, almost bringing the brush head to a stop in some cases.

The Accessory Brush Heads
I thought that the pumice head was much too rough to be used on the tender skin of the face. This would be a good one for use in exfoliating the skin on the legs, elbows and feet except that the motor speed is too slow to do a good job with the pumice head on these areas.

The crude polish accessory less rough than the pumice head, and better used for elbows and feet. The slow speed of the motor makes using this head rather ineffective when applying any pressure as the speed slows down too much.

I liked the latex soft sponge for applying face cream and foundation. It did a smooth, even job and with a bit of soap and water the head washed up well.

The make-up sponge did a good job of working make-up remover into the skin and taking the make-up off.

The rolling massager just seemed gimmicky to me. My skin didnâ€™t feel any different after using it. It just sounded like plastic rubbing on plastic while it was in motion and not like a very high quality device.

The short brush head seems to work well for removing loose dead skin cells.

The softer longer brush head also helped to remove loose dead skin cells.

I did not think that all these brush heads were necessary to be included in this kit. They were all quite novel but I think over time the use of some of them would fall by the wayside.

There are replacement heads that can be purchased when the heads that come with the kit wear out. The brush heads appear to be fairly durable. I could find no information regarding antibacterial qualities of the brush heads or of how often the heads should be replaced.

My conclusion: I would not recommend purchasing this item as it is severely underpowered and the handle is not waterproof, leading to a risk of getting water into the battery when the device is in use. Some of the brush heads are useful, others are gimmicky and others will be hard to use because of the underpowered motor. For the one or two brush heads that are useful, this device is not worth spending the money.by the wayside.

column6: Trichloroacetic Acid Solution TCA 80% Concentrated Chemical Skin Peel
column14:
Well, the product works but what it takes to use it is a challenge. "Step 1: Locate the strength of the stock solution you purchased in the column above. Sept 2: Locate the strength of your final desired concentration in the right column above. Step 3: Add the volume indicated of your stock solution to a Graduated Cylinder fill the remaining volume with purified water to the 10 ML mark on the Graduated Cylinder. Thoroughly mix solution"
You have to be a chemist to get this one right. Don't know of too many people that have Graduated Cylinders at home and know how to dilute up to 10 ML. Plus you have to purchase distilled water according to the directions. (I didn't). Pretty small vial for the price, but in comparing it to another product I bought...that had understandable directions by the way....it works well. Just be careful at all times when using it, its pretty toxic.

column14: OK, so I am a super picky consumerâ€¦ If I don't like something I'm going to leave a review about itâ€¦ I had very little hope for this root concealer working for me, as I had already tried it in multiple colors over the years and it never covered my grayâ€¦ Even though I left it on for the 15 minutes as per the directions for resistant grayâ€¦ A couple months ago I went from reddish-brown hair to a darker brown on my whole head which is more toward my natural colorâ€¦ Of course within a week the grays show against the dark brown.. I figured I'd give Clairol root another try and order the number for dark brownâ€¦ I put it on today for the first time and decided that I would risk it by leaving it on my roots for 30 minutes instead of the 15 that it instructedâ€¦ OMG!â€¦ what a difference it makes to leave it on 30 minutes on resistant gray!.. not only did it cover all of my gray for the first time but it completely blends in with what's left over of the reddish brown that I had previouslyâ€¦ In other words color 4, rocks! but if you have resistant grays you must leave it on 30 minutes minimum! just ordered three more boxes! now I will use this every three weeks in between my colors at the salonâ€¦ I could probably go over eight weeks between colors by using this every threeâ€¦ I'm thrilled with the results!

column6: Red Carpet Kolour Luminous Body Glow
column13: Amazing product, smooths blemishes and imperfections for a \natural\" look"
column14: It's like real-life photoshop. This is an amazing product. I used it in a variety of settings, and it just looks great. I bought it to use on my wedding day, and I used it on trial days leading up to it. The color goes on well (better with an foam applicator than your fingers) and is easy to spread while it's wet, but then it stays on. I didn't have any rub off even when it was directly under white. I can't speak to extreme heat or high humidity, but it worked well enough and looked good all day even though it was mid 80's outside, sunny, and with 60% humidity. I used this product to provide some continuity between my makeup on my face and my un-makeuped neck and chest. I didn't have any big blemishes or tan-lines to hide, but it very much helped my look seem natural instead of heavy makeup. I would recommend this to anyone for achieving a more-perfect natural look.

column6: Maybelline New York The Blushed Nudes,.
column13: Natural looking eye shadow, that looks good on me.
column14:
I bought this eye shadow at Walmart back in April of this year. Noticed it on Amazon few dollars cheaper.

My favorite colors out of this palette are the light gold and dark gold - #3 and #5 on the top. I use 3 as a highlighter, 5 as a lid shade. Then in the crease of the eye I use the bottom dark colors 3 - 6 on the bottom. The pink shades looks good on me when I wear white. The gold shades looks good when I wear black. I apply these shadows with make up brushes. EcoTool brushes, a highlighter brush, a small shadow brush, and a lid brush. I have a flat eyeliner brush that I use the darkest color on my lash line. It's best to use make up brushes and not the ones included in the palette. When make up is applied the right way, these shades will look amazing. One just got to know their colors and how to apply.

These eye shadows looks more natural on me. I am more of a natural kind of person, use lots of bronzer. My skin tone, eye color and hair color just fits perfectly with this eyeshadow palette. I have brown eyes, brown hair and light to med skin tone. I don't like dark colors or unnatural colors.

This eye shadow palette makes me look refreshed, polished and professional.

I am very happy with Maybelline New York The Blushed Nudes eye shadow.

column13: Fractionated Coconut Oil is my go to oil for so many things!
column14:
Fractionated coconut oil is probably one of my favorite things in the world. It's light, odorless, easily absorbed, moisturizing without being greasy, and offers all the antioxidant benefits of coconut oil without the risk of going rancid. I like to use it straight from the bottle to moisturize my skin after I swim because it absorbs quickly and won't leave my skin feeling greasy, and it's my go to oil for the home made anti-aging creams and sugar scrubs I like to make.

Ellie's Best Fractionated Coconut Oil is premium grade 100% pure and all natural, so it's perfect as a carrier oil, and it's virtually scent free so it won't interfere with the scent of the oil you blend it with. This also makes it a great natural massage oil that glides on like silk, absorbs well, leaves no oily residue, and won't stain the linens. Which brings me to a rather delicate subject. Fractionated Coconut Oil is an excellent personal lubricant because it's odor free, taste free, non-greasy, safe for all skin types, non-irritating, and doesn't stain the sheets.

Fractionated Coconut Oil can be used to extend and enhance the fragrance of home made soy candles, for making soaps, shampoo, conditioners, perfumes, body lotions, scrubs, and a wide range of products. I like to use it when making home made whipped Shea butter skin cream specifically because it has natural antioxidant and disinfecting properties, won't clog your pores, stays liquid, is extremely long lasting and won't go rancid. I've included a few pictures of us using this oil to make a new batch of face cream at home just so you can see how well it blends.

Ellie's Best Fractionated Coconut Oil comes in a 16oz size plastic bottle so there's no risk of it shattering if dropped, and I love that they include a pop up cap, a solid cap, and a pump dispenser at no additional cost! I was able to purchase this bottle at a promotional discount for evaluation and review purposes, and I think it's an excellent product at an excellent price. The bottle size is a great value and the pump makes it so easy to use. Is there is anything more versatile or skin loving than this oil? I don't think so. I cannot live without it!The bottle size is a great value and the pump makes it so easy to use. Is there is anything more versatile or skin loving than this oil? I don't think so. I cannot live without it!

column6: 28 Whitestrips Onuge | Lovely Smile Professional Quality - Double Elastic Teeth Whitening Strips - Revolutionary Advanced No Slip Technology - NEW Formula By Lovely Smile Premium Line
column14:
Tried this out and feel iffy about the product. The strip wasn't difficult to apply to my teeth and did stay in place. The problem is the strip did not stick evenly to my teeth, meaning that it did not stick and stay on to the the ends of my teeth, where two teeth are touching. It stuck to the main surface of the tooth, which is fine, except it only whitens where the strip has contact-this means if any saliva gets under the strip, which WILL happen, those spots won't be whitened. I will say that I did keep pressing the strip down into my teeth crevices to try to combat this, but it didn't really help.

The effect this had on my teeth was that the perimeter of the tooth on the sides stayed the same, and the center of the tooth was whitened. Clearly this is not the desired effect. Also, there were some whiter spots on the whitenened areas that stood out, but they faded after an hour.

I feel like since it doesn't whiten evenly, I am not going to continue to use the product. I'm too worried that my teeth will end up being patchy looking.

column6: Silk'n Blue Acne Solution Device
column13: Very time consuming to use and no discernible change in skin quality
column14:
I got this to review through the Amazon Vine program. I have had some trouble with breakouts around my chin and bottom of face, I think mostly because a new hair product I was using. Anyway, I stopped using the hair product and thought maybe using the Silk'n Blue would help clear up this breakout. I also breakout a lot during my monthly cycle and was hoping this would help with that as well.

In short I used it for a few weeks and didn't really notice much difference either way.

This is a nice sleek device, it lasts a week or so on one charge and comes with a nice stand. The blue LEDs turn on when the device is close to your face (you do have to power it on and then bring it close to your face for the lights to turn on). It's an interesting idea and similar to the Tanda (which I had previously used and had similar results with..that is to say not much change in skin quality).

The main downfall to this device is that is incredibly time consuming to use. Silk'n recommends treating the area for 2 minutes, 2 times a day for 6-8 weeks to see results. Since I am reviewing this for Vine I only have 30 days to try it. In reality though I only used it for a couple weeks once a day. With the 2 minute per area treatment time it was taking me about 30 minutes to treat my face (just chin area and forehead). It was just way too time consuming.

Additionally the area where you are holding it on your face gets pretty hot. Maybe this will be nice in the winter, but in the summer it just makes your whole body sweat. It's pretty uncomfortable and my skin was red and poofy when I was done with a treatment. I did the treatments at night and the poofiness and redness was gone by morning so it wasn't a huge deal..but my skin felt a bit raw.

I also had a bit of trouble getting the light to come on. I would turn it on and then wait a few seconds and put it up to my face, the light wouldn't come on. So I would turn it off and turn it back on and try again. It did this every time I used it, so it always took a few minutes to get it running.

In the end I noticed absolutely no change in skin quality. If you have really severe acne this might work better but for my occasional breakouts it didn't seem to be all that effective. I personally don't have to time to keep using this giving the lack of benefit I was seeing with it.

Pros:
- Sleek looking and easy to hold
- Only have to charge weekly
- Nice stand and charger
- Didn't make my skin worse

Cons:
- Made my skin very hot, in the summer this made me uncomfortable and sweaty
- Left my skin red and poofy and sensitive right after use (this went away by the next morning)
- Took forever to treat a small area
- Didn't notice any change in skin qualityd turn it back on and try again. It did this every time I used it, so it always took a few minutes to get it running.

In the end I noticed absolutely no change in skin quality. If you have really severe acne this might work better but for my occasional breakouts it didn't seem to be all that effective. I personally don't have to time to keep using this giving the lack of benefit I was seeing with it.

Pros:

- Didn't notice any change in skin quality

column6: PURA D'OR Hair Loss Prevention Premium Organic Argan Oil Shampoo,16 Fluid Ounce (Packaging may vary)
column13: ... for over 4 months now and I am very pleased. I do notice a subtle change in my ...
column14: I have been using this shampoo for over 4 months now and I am very pleased.  I do notice a subtle change in my hair growth and I plan on continuing to use it long-term.  Obviously this is my own personal anecdote about the product and nothing will ever really prove their claims about hair growth like a large study, but what company has the funding for that?  I think for a shampoo, it is an excellent option if you are concerned about hair loss, but you should probably be realistic as far as the changes you expect to see, as with any shampoo product.  My hair feels softer and my scalp is not as dry and itchy as it used to be before using this shampoo.  The smell is not as pleasant as your typical shampoo but that is to be expected.  Overall I recommend this shampoo as an addition to your existing hair care regimen if hair loss is a concern.

column13: Prevents stinkage, but gets clumpy and pasty

When I looked it was just globs on on my pits. So I wiped it off and tried again, this time going really light a day doing my best to make it "glide" on which was nearly impossible. Thankfully I was able to return it (another star for that, I believe in companies who have great customer service and actually allow customers a risk free way to try their products). column6: Grave Before Shave Bay Rum Beard Oil 1 Ounce Bottle
column14:
Since I wrote the below, I've completely changed my mind. This beard oil is a total slow burn. The fragrance almost seems to come into its own after a few uses. I can definitely pick up the bay rum now, and the oil has grown to be much less flowery than my initial assessment. This oil has grown on me to the point it has become my go to beard oil. The scent becomes your own, and it goes on and soaks in so naturally. So glad I stuck with this!

Meh. I normally use Honest Amish beard oil, which I love, but wanted to give this stuff a try. Especially due to the Rum Bay scent. Living by the beach, I thought this would be the perfect compliment to my beard.

Let's just say, at this point I'm not too impressed.

The scent was nothing at all Bay Rum like. It's almost...flowery. Like roses, maybe. My daughter loves it, and that's great. But she's a six year old girl. Not exactly the manly, pirate-esque aroma I was expecting. Don't get me wrong though, the scent wasn't offensive, it just wasn't at all what I expected. And it was really strong for the first two hours. After that, it wasn't bad. But again, not at all Bay Rum-like.

On a positive note, I really like how the oil went on...felt good in my beard and not at all greasy. However, it didn't work any magic on my beard's actual appearance though. Maybe it just needs long term use for any effect. As a comparison, the oil from Honest Amish, which smells better, also has a marked improvement on how my beard looks after just one application.

column14: After reading many many reviews I decided to spend a decent amount of money on a set of clippers. They cut very nice and I purchased a #2 metal blade as well and loved the way it worked. However the third time I went to use them the motor started making a loud weird noise. The noise would come and go but it definitely didn't sound good. Luckily I still had one day left where I could return them to Amazon and not have to send them to Oster for warranty work. From the other reviews it seems like the LE has heat up issues, but I would imagine the motor noise issue is isolated. Who knows though. Not what I expected from a $130 set of clippers that cost a lot more than that in the local stores.

column6: Emjoi eRase e60 Dual Opposed Heads 60-Disc 2-in-1 Electric Epilator Tweezer with Shaver/Trimmer and Sensitive Attachments
column14:
This is my third epilator in 10 years. The first wore out after 3 years, the second was cordless, which seemed like a good idea, but the cordless ones won't work when plugged in (and I don't take long enough showers to epilade in the shower anyway), so when the rechargeable battery wouldn't hold a charge any more, it was toast. Took about two years for that to happen, at which point I gave up and started shaving again. When stubble and expensive razors got old I bought this Emjoi. I love it. Maybe I am just happy to be getting rid of hair cheaply and at the root again, but this thing makes me happy. I have only used it about 5 times so far, but this is what I have noticed:
1. It is powerful and the tweezers work well.
2. You can use it in a circular motion which seems to get more hairs.
3. It's very compact and easy to hold and store.
4. It doesn't need to have the limiting guard on it for it to be comfortable to use (you know after getting used to removing hair this way!) so it feels like it pulls more hairs in each sweep than the ones I have had in the past.
5. Easy to clean.
6. Works well on legs and underarms, haven't tried anything else.
7. A 20-30 minutes leg session once every 7-10 days keeps me pretty clean.
8. My husband things it is too loud

column6: The Honest Company - Sunscreen Lotion SPF 30, 3 Fl Oz
column14: I have been using the Honest brand sunscreen for almost two years and it has worked excellent & when I say that, I mean excellent for any sunscreen not just natural sunscreens.  I have had skin cancer & so I need a product that works & has much safer ingredients than then other chemical based sunscreens.  I have used both the old formula & recently have been using the new formula purchased at Costco with the same excellent results.  This past weekend I applied the new formula to my 3yr old son & he was in & out of the water for 2-3 hours without any redness.  I applied to myself & I was out in the sun for 3-4 hours with no redness.  I wanted to give my review so people will not be scared away from using this product by recent bad reviews on the Today Show.  Having watched parents not properly apply sunscreen over & over again, it is my guess that that there is a very good chance that it was â€œuser errorâ€ , not applying enough or not applying it soon enough (30 min before sun exposure) are the two most common errors I have witnessed.  Another failure could be product separation which can be fixed by kneading the tube to mix it.  If this product can protect a 45 year old bald surfer with pale skin, then it should be fine for everyone, just remember to read the directions when applying.

column13: My hair is softer and shinier after just a few days.
column14: As far as Argan Oil goes, this brand is great! I have a lot of different brands and I really like the fact that this is 100% Organic. In a world full of unnecessary additives, it is nice to see companies getting back to the basics. I have been using this oil for several days now not only on my hair, but on my hands, face, and even my lower abdomen where I have stretchmarks.  While it is too soon to see significant changes, my hair is feeling softer and looks shinier and my nails are not dried out from this Texas heat. I personally like adding just a little to my conditioner and letting it set on my hair while I shower. While my hair is damp, I add about a drop or two before heat styling. There is no smell which I like since I would rather it not compete with my body spray. The bottle is large, however a little goes a long ways so it should last quite a while. The top is a dropper so it is easier to control how much you use at a time and eliminates waste. All around, it seems to be a great product and I will continue to use it in hopes to see better results where my stretchmarks are concerned. I did receive this product for free to test and review and do recommend it.

column6: Kai Skylight Candle
column13: ... ago as a housewarming gift and immediately fell in love with it
column14:
I was given a Kai Skylight Candle almost a year ago as a housewarming gift and immediately fell in love with it... and that was before I even unwrapped the package. The candle itself absolutely did not disappoint. The Kai candle comes in a clean and happy green box that screams of "fresh and crisp but not overpowering" and that's exactly how the candle smells. It reminds me of a breezy, spring day in an idyllic setting outdoors and conjures images of standing in a garden at Versailles or gazing at the ocean from a plush yard with rolling hills.

In the past I found it challenging to find good candles with mild but lovely, fresh scents (most are too heavily fragrant with perfumes). When the Kai Skylight candle burns, it has a modest, pleasingly fresh and slightly floral scent. This candle also has a very slow and clean burn, leaving no mess. It is suitable for year-round use and my guests always ask about it and then order one for themselves.

I have ordered multiple Kai Skylight Candles to give as gifts and always make sure to have a few in inventory at my home. I hope they never discontinue this scent as I've found my go-to candle for any occasion.

column13: Really like that it is 100% natural and has no added fragrances
column14: (free sample supplied for review purposes)  We really like that it is 100% natural with no added fragrances.  At this time have only used it as a moisturizer and am happy with the results.  It does take some time to soak in so you will probably need to wait a half an hour before putting on your clothes.  For me I see this getting more use as a moisturizer during the dry winter months on my hands and lower legs because I don't like using other moisturizers that have chemicals added.  We also like to use essential oils so the idea of using this as a base for our own natural essential oils is very appealing to us.  We grow lots of flowers in our yard and the plan is to use some of those and am actually excited about doing that and will update when that happens.  We love Ellie's Best Fractionated Coconut Oil.

column6: Gillette AltraPlus Razor with Lubrastrip, 10 Count, Mens Razors / Blades
column13: Fantastic razors. So much better for me than the fancy ones.
column14:
I don't shave often and when I do I only shave my neck. I use an electric head razor to trim the rest of my face but I need to have a smooth neck. My skin is super sensitive and I've tried every brand of razor. I've tried the triple blades, the quadruple blades, and the vibrating diamond coated 99 blade monstrosities that are pitched as the best razors ever. I always end up with red bumps on my neck no matter what I use. I decided to get these when I saw them on sale one day. They are fantastic. They only have 2 blades and a little strip of gel to help them slide. I don't know how they do it but these blades cut so smooth and effortlessly. I can use them about 10 times before I throw them away which for me is about a month. The only downside is that if you keep them in the shower and they stay wet they will rust after a couple weeks. All razors seem to do this so it's not really a con.

If you have sensitive skin and want an easy shave try these out, you'll be glad you did.

column6: Zen IMMUNE BOOST ESSENTIAL OIL BLEND. Topical & Aromatherapy Organic Oils to Encourage Detox, Wellness & Strong Immune System. With Oregano, Cinnamon, Eucalyptus, Clove, Frankincense & More
column13: This is a great blend of essential oils to help boost the immune system!
column14: I have just gotten into essential oils and use most of them in a diffuser, so I was very excited to try this immune boast essential oil blend that I could use topically. I love using natural remedies and I have noticed some great results with the essential oils I have used so far. It seems like since entering perimenopause, my immune system doesn't work as well as it used to, so I find myself not feeling all that great quite often. I like that this blend contains the carrier oils, Jojoba Oil and Sunflower Oil, so I can use it directly on my skin. I did not realize the importance of carrier oils when I first started. Most of the essential oils contained in this blend have antiviral, antibacterial, antifungal, antiparasitic, antioxidant, and anti-inflammatory properties, making it great to help boost the immune system. I have used some of the essential oils on their own, but never in a blend like this. I absolutely love the smell of this oil blend. It's hard for me to describe because it contains so many different fragrant oils and none of them overpower any of the others. They just combine to make an amazing scent. I have used this oil on the bottoms of my feet at night and I have also inhaled it. The only thing that bothers me about using it on my feet, is that the oil gets on my sheets. I don't like wearing socks to bed, so I am not sure how I am going to get around this. I would rather use it on my feet during the day. I have felt a difference since using this though. I have been feeling much better and stronger, so I look forward to seeing how I feel a month from now. I received this oil blend at a discount in exchange for my honest review.

column13: Like a hot knife through butter
column14: Iâ€™ve been cutting my own hair once every 2 weeks for over 10 years now. I started with the Remington HC-80 which lasted for about 5 years until I plugged them into a 220 outlet in Europe and fried the motor. I then bought the Remington HC-822 which lasted me another 5 years until the guard that I use broke.( I always do my whole head with a #1) I went looking for replacement guards which are obviously not available so then I started looking for a new set of chippers with robust replicable guards. I ran across these at Meijer and noticed they had metal clips on the guards so I decided to make the purchase. Let me tell you that these are great clippers. Out of the box they feel very heavy duty and well made. When you turn them on its like firing up a piece of machinery, I can tell they are built to last. My first cut was the easiest cleanest cut Iâ€™ve ever done. The clippers glide through my hair with absolutely no resistance. Touching my hair afterward I can tell that the hair is cut clean; I like to rub my hand around after a fresh cut and it feels smooth and soft compared to my old clippers that left my head feeling rough. I would highly recommend these clippers.

column6: Crest 3D White Brilliance Value Pack - Brilliance Toothpaste 4.1 oz & Polishing Treatment 3 oz Mesmerizing Mint
column14: This is a two step toothpaste system meant to get your teeth as white as they can be and to maintain it through daily brushing. The first step is a deep cleansing toothpaste containing fluoride that removes stains like coffee, tea, wine etc from your teeth. this is used for one minute. Then without rinsing you use the second step, again for one minute, which is a whitening finisher in gel form which contains hydrogen peroxide. This is the step that actually whitens your teeth. I've been using this system twice a day for about two weeks. I like it. I have noticed whiter teeth, but more importantly I have had minimal sensitivity. I'm really sensitive to whitening strips and most whitening toothpastes and usually am not able to use them for more than a week without having to discontinue because of pain. I'm not sure if decoupling the cleaning and whitening steps is the reason for this, but so far, so good. Crest claims that the system keeps your smile up to 99% as white as a professional polish. My results have been more subtle, but definitely noticeable. I got this product for free thanks to Crest and BzzAgent.

I started noticing a difference in the brightness of my teeth within a couple days and it only got better over the following weeks. Unlike most toothpastes it requires a little effort to use. There are two bottles and you brush with step 1 (the cleaner) for a minute, spit out the toothpaste (donâ€™t rinse!), then brush with step 2 (the whitener) for 1 minute. I have a Sonicare toothbrush that beeps every 30 seconds so it was easy for me to know when I need to switch from top to bottom on my mouth or switch toothpastes. If I were to use a manual toothbrush I could see this toothpaste being a pain. The only real complaint I have about this toothpaste is the fact that you have to stop midbrush to switch toothpastes. Some of the other blades offered are very cheap and gimmicky like the "Gillette GOAL" blade which has a cartoon of a soccer player giving me the thumbs up... For my money, the Lord Superior platinum gave me a good enough shave that I can just throw the rest out. Shark was just as good and Feather acceptable. Crown wasn't bad either. As I said, good blades and bad - but most you won't even be able to find for sale, so one would be best off going with a strong, popular brand that sells in bulk here on Amazon.

column6: Italia Deluxe Ultra Fine Lip Liner set (Pack Of 12)
column13: ) Some have a nice creaminess to them which is much different than other ...
column14:
I use these lip liners as lipstick most of the time! (Easy to carry in my purse and take up little or no room!)

Some have a nice creaminess to them which is much different than other lip liners I've bought. A few are a bit dryer, but I can still blend them without a problem. And they don't come off as easily as most lip sticks do. All of the pencils are the size of a standard lead pencil and don't shatter when sharpened.

The colors are rich, with a nice range, and can be as bright as you'd like or very subtle - your choice. They also blend with each other nicely- I try to keep a matte look, so I use my finger to do the blending.

My only quibble is that some of the darker shades are nearly identical. It would be nice if there had been a few more pinks/fuchsias instead of half of the pencils being dark, but that is a minor matter I can work around.

All in all, these are a versatile product and a fine addition to anyone's makeup kit.

column6: Emerson Healthcare 817006 6-oz. Original Anti Monkey Butt Powder
column14:
Bought some of this ahead of a family trip to Disney World. I'm a big guy and the trip was scheduled for June. So, yeah. I knew things were gonna get swampy.

This product works well for that.

It doesn't last forever, of course, so I went into the trip anticipating that I'd want to carry a little canister of the stuff into the theme parks with me each day, so I could "reload" or re-freshen things up periodically throughout the day. (I wish I could've found a smaller, "travel" size bottle for taking into the parks. The standard bottle is huge. And putting it into a generic unmarked canister made me wonder if the security people would think I was bringing in drugs or something.)

Aside from freshening up things downstairs, I also occasionally found it useful for sprinkling it onto my sandals (reducing the friction between my foot and the sandal).

Obviously it gets messy, especially if you're applying it liberally. If you're slapping it on in your hotel room or a bathroom stall, you can expect to leave a big powdery mess behind when you're done. Nothing you can do about that, I guess.

When I went through the first airport on that trip, I got stopped by security as they wanted to run chemical tests on my Anti Monkey Butt bottle. Maybe the security guy was just bored and felt like breaking up the monotony in his day by busting out his drug test kit and playing "CSI" for a few minutes. Or maybe I just look like the kind of person who is going to try smuggling a soda-can sized bottle full of cocaine onto an airplane?

If you're taking this stuff with you on a trip, and you are worried about being held up at the security checkpoints, put it in a checked bag instead of your carry-on.

column6: TONYMOLY Backstage Gel Eyeliner #1 Black
column13: Not the best liner I've tried, but great for the price
column14:
I kept reading raving reviews about how this liner literally does not budge/flake off/smudge/etc, how amazingly pigmented it is, etc etc., so of course I had to give it a shot. Given the virtually unanimous praise for this product, it was slightly underwhelming.

PIGMENTATION: I like my black liners to be pitch-black--like opaque, matte, and literally black. I found this product to be a little weak in that regard--it had a slightly glossy finish, and wasn't really as black and opaque as I would have liked. In fact, I had to build it up and apply it a couple times for me to be satisfied with the pigmentation. In this regard, it's definitely worse than my current 'holy grail' liner, the Tarte clay gel liner.

LONGEVITY: Definitely lasts a decent amount of time, but it isn't smudge-proof. It also takes quite a while to set, so don't touch your eyes for a few minutes after applying this product. However, in terms of longevity, I have to say this performs slightly better than my Tarte clay gel liner (which tends to get dry/flaky as the day progresses).

This liner definitely lasts a long time, but because it didn't have the sort of pigmentation I expect from a liner, it's not something I would use too often unless, say, it's raining outside and I need something more waterproof. For the price, you can't beat it though!

column6: Palmers Palmers Cocoa Butter Lotion for Stretch Marks
column13: Bought this lotion after reading reviews and although many people rate this a bad product they tend to think the lotion should w
column14: I started to work out not too long ago and as a result I got stretch marks near my back end of my biceps towards the armpit and had a fair share of stretch marks in my upper thighs. Bought this lotion after reading reviews and although many people rate this a bad product they tend to think the lotion should work instantly or remove stretch marks permanently, but it doesn't. You'll need to apply this lotion twice a day and make sure no clothing or any fabric touches the area as it will rub off, I personally just went shirtless or naked most days with fans on to make it dry out on my skin faster. I started to notice my stretch marks getting lighter and in tone with my skin color after 2 months and with a tan setting in they're barely even noticeable. NOTHING will get rid of stretch marks permanently (maybe laser treatment), you can only get them lighter with skin care products such as this one. My stretch marks are red as I am light skin color, just don't give up after a week or two just keep at it, twice a day.  Hope this review helps.

column6: Pure Body Naturals Cold Pressed Castor Oil for Hair Growth & Skin Care, Hexane-Free, 16 Fl. Oz
column14: I've been fighting scalp folliculitis  for three years.  The most successful preparation had been colloidal silver spray which usually controlled the condition but couldn't seem to cure it. I suspect the preparation didn't reach the hair follicles very well but did a lot to kill surface bacteria.  Then, I read about possible side effects of colloidal silver and sought an alternative.  Castor Oil for Natural Skin and Hair arrived three days ago.  The first night, I used too much and pretty much saturated my hair.  My folliculitis was in an unusual and painful flareup, though, so I just kept the Castor Oil in overnight.  Yes, this is an oil, so it does feel heavy, especially in summer heat, and has a little odor (the odor is far less unpleasant than some medicated shampoos), but by the next morning, my scalp was smooth, and the problem areas were either going or gone.  On the two subsequent applications, I've used teardrop-sized amounts on my fingertips and massaged the oil thoroughly into my scalp to prevent greasy buildup on my hair.  That's working better; a little oil goes a long way.  Three applications, and my scalp is completely clear and calm.  It even FEELS like a normal, healthy scalp with no bumps or scaling.  That weird prickling/itching feeling that signals a new flareup is disappearing, too. I feel a little itching, but there's nothing there!  Perhaps the oil is able to penetrate the skin enough to reach the infected follicles and really stop this condition.  I don't know yet if Castor Oil will cure the infection or just contain it, but it was so shockingly effective, I wanted to comment right away.

column6: Medibead
column14:
I needed to find a replacement for my moist heat pad from The Happy Company. I wish they still made their products as it was really nice, and I purchased several for my family as well as for gifts. Unfortunately, they no longer make the large heating pads, so I searched for something that was comparable. I was unable to find something as large as the one that I currently had which covered the entire back, but this heat pad was still a good size. The other thing that I needed was something that did not have a lavender scent built into the heating pad which this did not.

This heating pad is easy to use. You just pop it into the microwave for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes, and it stays hot/warm for 20 to 30 minutes. If you need to use it for longer periods of time, you just pop it back into the microwave for another minute. It has a good weight to it which also helps with the muscle aches and cramps.

My previous heating pad had a removable, washable cover, but the heating pad itself was not washable. This heating pad does not have a removable cover, but it is washable by hand. You just need to make sure that the heating pad has not been used in the last 2 hours as it needs to be completely cool before you wash it. It also need to dry out for 24 hours after you wash it before you can use it again. That's important to keep in mind if you need to have the heating pad available on a regular basis.

Even in our dry desert climate, the heating pad still gives off a nice moist heat. I like that, unlike my previous heating pad, the MediBeads do not give off a scent after the pad is microwaved.

column6: L'OrÃ©al Paris Revitalift Triple Power Day Lotion SPF 20, 1.7 fl. oz. (Packaging May Vary)
column13: Works On My Problem Areas With Quick Results
column14:
This product claims to reverse the ill effects of aging skin such as dark spots and wrinkles. If it did do this it would be worth a lot more money than is being charged here.
I use a lot of skin care products, mostly due to the fact that I am offered a lot of unique and some rather ordinary products through the Vine program. Not all of them are great, but using a moisturizer normally will minimally offer hydration. It'll plump up skin and make it look better.
This product promises the following:
Repairs wrinkles
Smooth out fine lines
Fade spots plus discoloration
As it applies to me I have genetically good skin and I have never smoked and I rarely drink alcoholic beverages. I look younger than my actual age and rarely go outside without sunscreen.
This Revitalift production has a nice scent and isn't thick nor greasy. It spreads evenly when lightly massaged into the skin and does a good job hydrating. My skin looks fuller and thicker and possibly even brighter. Could it be that the moisturizing effects reflect off the skin's surface? I don't have dark spots. Wrinkles? Nothing severe, but everything is moisturized and softened.
The biggest selling points are this product offers dependable moisturization for the full day. It is not heavy nor is it greasy when used as instructed. It also contains an SPF of 20 which might be an issue if you spend excessive amounts of time of time in the sun and sweat a lot.
I'd buy this for its hydrating properties alone and am glad it has the sunscreen for protection. Does it eliminate dark spots? I have no way to verify that, but this is a nice product that manages to soften and refresh the skin.

column6: Ultimate Smile Professional At-Home Teeth Whitening Kit
column14:
Of all the professional and OTC teeth whiteners I've tried over the years, none have worked as well as the Ultimate Smile system. The kit is similar to the one I received after having a Zoom treatment and worked as well, if not better.

The kit comes with a customizable mouthpiece and 2 5mL syringes of whitening gel. Since I already had custom trays from the Zoom kit, I didn't use the trays that came with this kit.

For each treatment, you'll place 5 mL (total top and bottom) of gel into the trays and wear for 15 minutes. During the 15 minutes, I did not experience any sensitivity or discomfort. After the 15 minutes, remove the trays and rinse to reveal your whiter smile.

The price of this kit is less than what most whitening strip kits costs making it a great value. This is a product I would recommend to anyone looking for whiter teeth.

Disclaimer: I received this kit free of charge to review and all opinions are those of the author.

column6: Cosrx Bha Blackhead Power Liquid
column13: Great product for reducing pores and smoothing skin
column14:
Great product for reducing pores and smoothing skin. Even after 4 months of use (I'm barely half way through the bottle) I'm still seeing results.
Initially I had some purging but after about two weeks it quit.
How I Use it: I first wash my face with a PH 5.5 cleanser, apply this immediately, let it sit for 20 minutes to let it work. After 20 minutes I don't wash it off, I just apply the rest of my routine. I found not washing it off works best for me. If I apply a vitamin c serum before this, I find it never completely sinks in. If I use this on bare skin, in 20 minutes it will mostly absorb into my skin. Doesn't leave an oily residue or a heavy feeling, just a light layer.
When I first started out I only used it every 2 days. After 2 weeks, when the purging stopped, I started using it every other day. After another 2 weeks I started using it everyday.
At first I thought it was a "meh" product, but using it consistently is whats making the difference in cleaning out and keeping my pores clean.
Its also very gentle, I have eczema and while I did feel a little tingle around my nose, (where its most sensitive), I didn't notice any irritation. After 3 weeks, my skin is smoother than ever, my pores aren't invisible, but much, smaller/cleaner,
Pros: Light, easy to use
Somewhat gentle
Made my skin much smoother
Made my skin tone brighter
Helped reduce pores
Has helped prevent and heal acne
Cons: It never completely absorbed, left a slight film on my face

column14: I would have given 5 stars except for the fact that Philips purposely engineers their toothbrushes to crap out with no chance of fixing them yourself or replacing the battery shortly after the warranty expires - you pretty much have to go buy a brand new toothbrush 1-2 years later. For the price point, that is NOT acceptable by any means, which is why I implore you: REGISTER THE TOOTHBRUSH AS SOON AS YOU GET IT!! You will have a much easier time getting your product RMA'd if need be, and you will have documentation to back up your claims, so customer service will be much more likely to help you. Also, doing so extends your mfctr warranty by 6 months, so it becomes a 2.5-year warranty. I had a DiamondClean years ago which broke 1 month after the 2-year warranty expired (how convenient!) and was hesitant to go back to Philips. That being said, the Flexcare Plus is just FANTASTIC. The battery life alone is amazing - I received it a week ago with 3/4 battery charge, been using it twice a day since then and still has two bars left, have yet to fully charge it. I was previously using an Oral-B Deep Sweep $25 rechargeable brush from CVS; charging took 16 hours and only gave you 1.5 weeks of use at most, and while it did a good job cleaning my teeth, it rattled my entire skull! The Sonicare lineup in that aspect is awesome - very intense but super-precise sonic vibrations, so it does not rattle your head while brushing. My teeth feel amazingly smooth and clean all day/night into the next morning, and does a good job massaging your gums. I also like that it flexes to get around the sides of your back-most teeth, which I have always had a hard time cleaning. Wish it came with a UV cleaner, but I'm very satisfied nonetheless. My teeth are at least 5 shades whiter, and it has also lessened the brown plaque lines I have between my teeth (GROSS!!) from all the coffee I drink each morning. Thumbs up all around! I will update again should anything change, or break...

column6: Salicylic Deep Gel Exfoliating Cleanser - Enhanced with Tea Tree Oil & Green Tea Extract (Professional) - Peel Prep
column13: Found my morning routine and this is a staple
column14: Love this product. Since 2013 I have been on a mission to find the right cleansing/moisturizing/treatment routine for my skin.  I have mature, combination normal/oily skin with acne on my cheeks and whiteheads on my nose plus I have cystic acne.  I learned my skin is more sensitive than I ever thought and I learned the hard way what I can't use.  During my trials, my skin would clear up and then to my chagrin, acne and hyper pigmentation would come roaring back to my face bigger and badder than before I tried to find something to help.  Out of all that I learned what I can use and Salicylic Deep Gel Exfoliating is now a staple for me. This is one of my cleansers and I use it every three days.  It helps to keep my outbreaks under control.  If I have a pimple that is starting to become painful, I use this cleanser two or three days in a row.  For me, this is the only treatment I need for now for my cystic pimples and they clear up quickly (3 â€“ 4 days).  Far better than a doctorâ€™s visit.  Other days I use a gentler cleanser - Collagen Facial Cleansing gel.  These two together work in conjunction to keep my face clean without abusing my skin.  I imagine it is the tea tree in salicylic cleanser that helps me.  The smell is not great but I donâ€™t like the smell of tea tree anyway.  I use a dime size amount and depending on the oiliness of my skin, I either use my cleansing brush or my hands to wash my face.  I use a gentle hydrating toner and a regular oil skin moisturizer (Neutrogena).  I also use a very mild peel 2X a month.  I do not use this cleanser on a day that I use the peel.  The two together are a little strong for me.  When I purchased the cleanser, it was not labeled as a â€œPre-Peelâ€.  So now my second purchase (with coupon), my cleansing routine will remain the same even though the name of the product has changed.  I gave it a 5 but I would also like to note that my face is not entirely clear.  No more whiteheads EVER but blackheads show up from timeto time.  I donâ€™t expect the cleanser to do the whole job by itself.  I do know this cleanser keeps the cysts at bay also.  It has saved me a few doctorsâ€™ visits for the cysts, so this product is a winner.

column14:
How do you compare the hundreds of skin care products? As a regular tester, I've arrived at a list of key considerations. I hope these are helpful to you!

~ Fragrance: Herbal, menthol scent. No added fragrance.
~ Feel during application: Smooth, like a light to medium-weight lotion. Cooling.
~ Feel after absorption: There is a sharp feeling that is both cold and hot; it feels more cold than hot to me personally. I find this sensation to be pleasant. It doesnâ€™t leave a sticky film, and skin feels smooth after application.
~ Is it best for a certain skin type?: Should be fine for all.
~ Is it tested on animals?: No.
~ Packaging: 4oz plastic wide mouth tub with screw top lid.
~ Immediate cosmetic effects:* None.
~ Potential long-term effectiveness:* This product has probably the longest list of essential oils in its ingredients that Iâ€™ve ever seen. Iâ€™m not going to even try to recite them all! But let me put it this way: Thereâ€™s no way this cream isnâ€™t going to do *something* good for you. Whether that happens to be reducing cellulite ....Iâ€™m sceptical that any cream can do that, Iâ€™ll get back to you if this does. But it will be excellent for your skin and possibly even your overall health. Think covering yourself with the strongest and most diverse herbal poultice ever. Iâ€™d also use this on the chest and throat for colds, and on sore muscles. This formula includes some very expensive skin care essential oils like Roman chamomile and helichrysum.

IMPORTANT: You DO NOT want this stuff in your eyes. Wash your hands after application! It contains capsaicin, black pepper, cinnamon, and ginger in potent forms. These are all powerful irritants that wonâ€™t damage mucous membranes but they will burn with a vengeance.

*Know the difference between cosmetic and long-term effects: Cosmetic effects are immediate and only present when the product has been applied recently - just like makeup. Long-term effects take longer to see and should remain when you stop using the product (but don't when you find something effective - your skin needs continuing support). The ideal product would be both cosmetically and long-term effective, but it's more realistic to expect a formula to tilt towards one or the other.

column13: It is easy to apply and applies like a liquid eyeliner
column14:
I am posting a review five days in to keep track of progress but also intend to do edit and update this review at the end of 30 days.

08/02/2015 5 day update:
I have been applying this lash serum every morning when I wake up, before I do my makeup and every night before I sleep.
It is easy to apply and applies like a liquid eyeliner. Read the instructions! At first it took some getting the hang of it; if you apply too much it will run into your eyes and burn. The instructions say to moisten the lash line, but do not saturate. As long as it looks wet, it's enough.
I apply it to my bottom and top lashlines and sparse areas of my eyebrows.
While I haven't noticed a significant amount of growth yet, I have definitely noticed how much more healthy and nourished my eyelashes and eyebrows look.
They feel strong , and not flimsy and have a thicker appearance as well. Mascara looks better and more fluffy because of how healthy my eyelashes look. They have grown very slightly, but I am happy with the results so far.

column14: I've been using this serum for a year and have gone through many bottles. I loved it. I'm a skin care snob and have tried every department store luxury skincare line and most infomercial brands. Nothing moisturized my skin as this vitamin c serum helped to do. I felt using as a first step helped the rest of my skincare absorb and work magic. My usual skincare regimen without this serum was unsatisfactory, but in combination with this serum gave amazing results! I have sensitive skin due to preventative acne ointments used since high school (now mid 30's.) My acne prone skin stayed at bay and I never had a breakout.. Until now. The formula of this serum has changed. Original formula was a thin liquid, transparent and odor free. New formula is thick, sticky, dark yellow and has a foul fishy odor. I thought maybe I had received a bad batch so I reordered, and unfortunately received the same new consistency. Truly disappointed. I'm sad the original formula is gone and now my dry flaky skin has come back along with horrible acne and redness the new formula left behind. Maybe it'll work for you if not acne prone. Surely didn't work for me.

Anyone who thinks 5 blades is simply a marketing gimmick, I urge you to think again. With the right technique, it is a very close, smooth shave.

column6: Lay-n-Go Cosmo Cosmetic Bag (20\)"
column14:
This bag is exactly what it claims: a washable cosmetic bag that converts into an easily transportable handled clutch. I can spread out my cosmetics on its clean surface as desired. It stays dry, and both the lip and the fact that it's not a smooth hard surface prevent my things from rolling onto the floor.

Inside of the bag are a small pocket and an elastic band. I'm not sure why the elastic band isn't in all of Amazon's product images, but the elastic band did come with my Ocean Blue version and easily holds things like my brushes and my tweezers. The Lay-n-Go's material is washable, at least for the normal stuff I have spilled on it (eyeshadow, foundation, lotion, etc). Cleaning instructions are sewn into the outer velcro pocket. After each use, I'm able to simply pull the drawstring and the surface folds up into a clutch again.

I've included a picture of it folded and laying flat so you can get an idea of how much I've stuffed into it. Note that I also keep the little containing bag with me that the Lay-n-Go comes with just in case I need to further contain a mess since it isn't a 100% tight seal. That said, I've never needed to do it since I have been able to wipe off all of the messes I've made.

Photos:
- Lay-n-Go with a bunch of stuff on it just to give you an idea of the surface area
- Lay-n-Go with everything centered for folding up (can't really fit the brush and the contact lens solution in there when I fold it up without it being too open, but I usually stow the solution in a Ziplock anyway)
- Lay-n-Go folded up (yes all that stuff really is in there)
- Containing bag the Lay-n-Go comes in, just in case you want to use yours for something too.
- Location of the cleaning instructions

column13: A great addition to the medicine cabinet
column14: I originally got this for reducing the pore size of the pores around my nose and on my chin.  It works great for that.  But I wanted to mention something else in my review.  A couple of days ago, my neighbor was stung by a bee.  She must have some kind of mild allergy because the skin on her arm became very hard under the sting.  It hurt and stayed hot.  She was so uncomfortable and nothing seemed to work.  I thought about this and asked her if she wanted to try it.  She was ready to try anything.  We put the healing clay on her arm and left it one for about 25 minutes and then she washed it off.  I left the jar with her and she put more on right before bed.  The next day, the sting was so much better.  I'm glad I had this for her!  Yesterday my son had a very itchy mosquito bite and we did the same thing.  It was much better after just one treatment.  Although this is a great treatment to have around for your face, it is also good for the medicine cabinet to treat bites and stings.  I really like that the healing clay is from Wyoming.  I love domestic products :)
