column6: SURF SPRAY by It Hair Styling Spray Gives Beautiful Wavy Hair Texture and Windblown Volume Infused with Abyssinian Oil and Algae Triage Complex, Style and Enhance Collection, 5.1oz Spray
column14:
I've had awful luck in the past with hair products, my hair is very thick, heavy and has a very very slight kink. I generally either need a lot of product to get what I'd like my hair to do or it flat out just doesn't work for my hair. Being a stay at home mom I'd been looking for something easy and low maintenance that would give my generally flat hair some volume and body without making my hair feel crunchy/greasy.

When I saw Surf Spray by It, I decided to give it a shot and I was expecting it to fail like all the other spray in products. I have never been so glad to be wrong! Not only does it give my hair a nice texture it volumizes ALL DAY (will last for 2-3 days without a shower though it'll straighten out a bit). I was pretty amazed that it'd hold up my thick and heavy hair so such an extended period of time and the best part of all it left my hair SMOOTH. Not crunchy, greasy, or hard but soft and smooth; like I wasn't wearing any product at all. I didn't over use the product I flipy hair upside down after a shower and spray 4-5 times to make sure that all of my hair (back and front) has some product dispersed into it. Also it smells wonderful, it's a light refreshing scent that will softly linger in your hair without being overwhelming.

Overall I am very impressed with It Haircare and am looking forward to purchasing and trying other products from their line :)

I received this product at a discount in exchange for my honest and unbiased review, this does not effect the integrity of my review and I stand by my opinions of this product.

column6: Oral-B Pro-Health Precision Clean Battery Toothbrush for Superior Plaque Removal and Healthy Gums, Pack of 1
column13: Like it better than the Oral-B Pro 1000
column14:
When my seventeen year old Braun Oral-B electric toothbrush finally bit the dust (I presume the battery died), and it was time for a replacement, I decided to give the Pro 1000 rechargeable a try. I wasn't looking for any bells and whistles, just something that cleaned well and felt solid. I also ended up getting this one for travel, but found that I actually liked it better, and started using it every day. It's been six months now, and so far it has worked flawlessly. I haven't had any problems with the battery cover that others have mentioned. I usually use (older) Rayovac hybrid rechargeables, and have also used regular Energizers and have no difficulty getting the cover back on with either one. I also try to keep the handle clean so that crud does not build up on it.

This toothbrush does a great job on my teeth and gums, and it feels more like using my old one than the Pro 1000. I don't know if that unit is more powerful, or if it's just the 3D effect they advertize, but I find that the vibration is too aggressive. I have to use a sensitive brush head with it, or it feels like there's a jack hammer in my mouth. Aggressive brushing is not better brushing. With this one, the regular brush head works great (same kind I used for years on the older model), and I don't feel like I'm sand blasting my teeth. It also feels healthier for my gums, where you don't want anything too aggressive. Provided the battery cover holds up, I would definitely recommend this model. I also like the convenience of not having something else to plug in on my counter, and I can get a couple of months of use out of my batteries before I have to recharge them. Can't beat the price either!

column6: Arctic Fox Semi Permanent Hair Dye - 4 Ounce Violet Dream #5
column14:
I have used Violet Dream two different ways.....

Scenario #1 - My hair was black and I wanted am hombre effect. So I bleached my ends to a yellowish blonde color and then covered them in Arctic Fox Purple Rain. Loved it! When it faded it was a really pretty plum fuschia like color. I liked the color so much I wanted to try to stick with that shade so I used Violet Dream on top of it. It really brightened up the plum shade that Purple Rain left behind. If you want a dark amethyst purple then use Purple Rain. If you want a fuschia purple then use Violet Dream.

Scenario #2 - My hair was a faded Age Beautiful 1V Plum Black hair. I wanted to lighten it this time around. So I did a bleach bath on my whole head. I got my hair to a coppery color and then dyed it Age Beautiful 4V which was a plum brown shade. The color was pretty and had a lot more red tones then purple. So I gave my hair a rest for a week and then threw Violet Dream on top and walla!! The PERFECT VIBRANT PLUM!

You can see my review as well as my faded color in my review of Purple Rain here: https://www.amazon.com/review/R11YW3KX35PGFR/.

column6: Bvlgari Omina Crystalline Women's EDP Eau De Parfum Spray - BOC9881411
column13: Explanation as to why your Parfum doesn't smell like you thought it would!
column14:
What is really unfortunate about this perfume, and what a lot of people on here are complaining about, is this:
The Eau De Toilette and the L'eau De Parfum are both Crystalline scented, but we've all been screwed because the difference between all toilette's and parfum's is huge, but the should always be the same. Toilette is cheaper, it doesn't stay on as long, and you have to keep re-spraying throughout the day. Parfums on the other hand, last all day and even into the next day if you don't wash your hair. With this product, we've been ROYALLY screwed over. The parfum smells nothing like the the toilette, we love the toilette smell WAY more than the parfum, but the toilette won't last long, while the same "Crystalline" in parfum will last all day, yet it smells so different. And, on top of everything, we're tricked by the titles of these products. "Eau De Toilette Perfume" ... That makes no sense! It's either/or, there's no such thing as a toilette perfume. So please don't be fooled by these types of product names when you see them. Toilette is toilette, parfum is PERFUME, it stays on, and is always more expensive. Toilette is always a cheaper way to have the perfume you love, except with Omnia Crystalline, we got screwed. We buy the perfume, we lose because the smell is different; we buy the toilette, we're screwed because it doesn't stay on all day.
I hope this helps explain the confusion and I hope it makes everyone start paying attention to the actual BOTTLE, not the product name that was written. Perfume and eau de toilette's are two very different things!!

column6: Williams Mug Shaving Soap - 1.75 oz
column13: Jason Voorhees would love Williams soap
column14: Williams was the first shaving soap I ever tried. I found some in another city on a holiday weekend, and bought three pucks to take home since I was running low on my Gillette cream and had recently switched to a double-edge blade. When the time came for my first soap shave, it didn't go well. The lather on Williams is just plain bad. I tried all the tricks and hacks to get the most out of this soap, because apparently it's a water hog and won't lather right unless you spoil it like a princess first. Even then, I ended up with a bad shave and cuts everywhere, and a lot of blood (that's where the title of my review came from, haw haw). There was little to no cushion which made for a rough glide. At first I thought that I had just done something wrong (even though I'm an experienced shaver), and so I waited to write this review until I could try again with a different soap. Yesterday I had my first shave with Arko, and that soap performed like a decent shaving soap should -- excellent lather, excellent cushion, and a seriously close shave with no cuts or irritation. I'd go so far as to say that it was the best shave I've ever had. So my recommendation is to go with Arko for an inexpensive soap and don't bother with Williams unless you're feeling masochistic. I rated Williams 2 stars instead of 1 because I know Williams has a market and it's been around for ages, and for that reason alone I at least give it some respect. But I cannot recommend a soap that I feel is more trouble than it's worth.

column14:
The pros:
Natural
Contains pure Manuka Honey
Works on acne spots, as well as bug bites
A very good all-around healing gel
Great for sensitive skin
Doesn't dry out surrounding skin
Not sticky at all like other Manuka products

The cons:
Smells horrible. Seriously. This smells so, so bad. I've used Manuka honey products and yes, they have a "natural" honey scent, because it's honey. But this one has something else in it that makes it smell very bad. You have to let it dry completely before applying makeup, but even then I can still smell it.
The consistency is very runny. When I unscrewed the lid, it kind of exploded and a lot started pouring out.
The tube is TINY. It is very very small, so it must be used sparingly.

Bottom line: I am using it, but very sparingly, because the tube is so tiny. I dab a little on a spot after washing my face, then wait at least thirty minutes before applying coverup or sunscreen. But at night I use a different product, because this one smells so bad it keeps me awake.

column6: Retseliney Peptide and Hyaluronic Moisturizer Cream with Vegan Hyaluronic Acid, Shea Butter, Green Tea, 1.7 fl oz / 50 ml
column13: Solid formulation for moisturizing and firming
column14:
How do you compare the hundreds of skin care products? As a regular tester, I've arrived at a list of key considerations. I hope these are helpful to you!

~ Fragrance: Very light lotiony smell, no added fragrance.
~ Feel during application: Smooth but not slippery or oily; like a light lotion.
~ Feel after absorption: Moister, but does not leave a sticky or oily film at all.
~ Is it best for a certain skin type?: Should be good for all. Very dry skin might need a heavier moisturizer as well. No irritation to my sensitive skin.
~ Is it tested on animals?: No.
~ Packaging: 2oz white plastic pump bottle. Pump dispenses smoothly and precisely.
~ Immediate cosmetic effects:* Minimal, skin is shinier and dry skin areas look nicely moisturized.
~ Potential long-term effectiveness:* Has good moisturizers including shea butter, jojoba oil, and aloe to keep skin conditioned. Active ingredients are hyaluronic acid, a particularly good blend of amino acids, and B5. This is labeled as a moisturizer that promotes skin firmness, and I would say itâ€™s an excellent formulation for exactly that. I'm a huge fan of shea butter in moisturizers as I've found it to be one of the single best ingredients for dry, irritated skin.

*Know the difference between cosmetic and long-term effects: Cosmetic effects are immediate and only present when the product has been applied recently - just like makeup. Long-term effects take longer to see and should remain when you stop using the product (but don't when you find something effective - your skin needs continuing support). The ideal product would be both cosmetically and long-term effective, but it's more realistic to expect a formula to tilt towards one or the other.

I received this free or virtually so for product testing and review. I am under no obligation to provide a positive review and receive no incentives or rewards for doing so. My aim is to highlight features and drawbacks that I would want to know about as a buyer, not hype the product for the manufacturer. My remarks are sincere and my own.uct for the manufacturer. column6: eb5 Intense Moisture Anti-Aging Cream
column14:
eb5 has the consistency of [[ASIN:B00430CRX6 NOXEMA clean cream]] but without the mediciney aroma.

Granted that one is for dry skin and the other's often used as make-up remover,
yet a quick comparison of ingredients is most revealing:

NOXEMA
Water (aqua), stearic acid, linum usitatissimum (linseed) seed oil, glycine soja (soybean) oil, fragrance (parfum), propylene glycol, gelatin, camphor, ammonium hydroxide, menthol, sodium bicarbonate, calcium chloride, magnesium sulfate, potassium chloride.

eb5
water (aqua), propylene glycol, tocopheryl acetate, mineral oil (paraffinum liquidum), stearic acid, cetyl alcohol, avena sativa (oat) kernel flour, phenoxyethanol, silica, aminomethyl propanol, carbomer, potassium sorbate, allantoin, ethylhexylglycerin, panthenol, retinyl palmitate

NOXEMA eems less exotic, somehow....safer. To wit....

eb5 GLOSSARY
Tocopheryl acetate is Vitamin E. This is the good stuff, for when it's absorbed in the skin there's evidence that it helps build a body's Vitamin E content.
Cetyl alcohol is fatty and is used as a thickener in cosmetics. (It's also used to oil nuts and bolts!)
Avena sativa is wild oats, commonly used to support hormone levels in men.
Carbomer is made from acrylic acid. Here it's used as a gel.
Phenoxyethanol is an insect repellent also a topical antiseptic.
Aminomethyl propanol is an acid neutralizer.
Potassium sorbate is a salt that inhibits dairy and wine mold. It's here to prevent the growth of microorganisms.
Allantoin is an unusual one. It's found in human urine because our bodies don't want it. (See WIKIPEDIA for manufacturers' claims of its benefits.)
Ethylhexylglycerin is frequently used to treat eczema and as a deodorizer.
The 2nd to last ingredient, Panthenol is a B5 acid that aids in moisturizing.
Retinyl palmitate is a synthetic Vitamin A. When ingested in large quantities it may accelerate the development of cancer (see WIKIPEDIA article), but it's a trace ingredient here.

Manufacturer's claims of \\\Allergy Tested, Non GMO (not genetically engineered), Vegan, Gluten Free and Never Tested on Animals\\\\\" are all well and good, however there's enough in the way of chemicals in eb5 to make necessary a safety warning of \\\\\"Discontinue use if irritation occurs.\\\\\"

I've been applying eb5 with no adverse effects to date, but if avena sativa causes my testosterone levels to spike or if cetyl alcohol cures my creaky joints, I'll let you know.he development of cancer (see WIKIPEDIA article), but it's a trace ingredient here.

column6: X Out Deluxe Wash-In Treatment with bonus Spot Corrector Acne Treatment
column13: Great product-- but it will bleach fabrics!
column14:
I bought this for my teenage daughter and, I have to say, it does work quite well. We saw dramatic results in the first week she began using it and her skin is noticeable clearer. While the product does work well, I gave it 4 stars because it also does stain (or bleach) clothes, towels, and even the paint on our bathroom wall! That's not such a problem when my daughter uses it in the shower, but you are supposed to use it twice a day. I suggest using a designated washcloth, when cleansing at the sink, to help reduce the amount of product being splashed around as you rinse your face.

The cleanser can be used as a face wash, a face mask, or applied to small areas to target individual pimples. It came with a small tube of spot corrector, which did not impress us. It is very runny and watery. We tried keeping it in the fridge (thinking maybe it was just especially runny after arriving in the mail on a particularly hot day), but it seems to stay runny. Since you can use the cleanser in the same way, we really haven't bothered with the spot corrector.

I was pleased to be able to find X-Out on Amazon, because I wanted to be able to try this cleanser without committing to a subscription that is automatically shipped-- and for which you are continually billed.

column6: Blue Cross Cuticle Remover 6 Oz
column13: A must for your manicure kit.

It dissolves the extra bit of cuticles stuck to your nails and the edges without any fuss, and allows you to easily push up the cuticle and create a nice clean edge. No more cutting cuticles! I actually used it and a small file to buff my cuticles down a little bit and buff off any excess on the nail bed and it worked like a charm. Have a towel underneath though because this stuff isn't thick at all. It's pure liquid so it will drip off of your hands. I have fairly sensitive skin too and this didn't bother me at all.

column13: I really can't recommend this product enough
column14: I really can't recommend this product enough! I have struggled with acne and oily skin for as long as I can remember and nothing has ever worked for me as well as Obagi. I have tried everything from Proactiv to dermatologist prescribed products ranging from antibiotics, retinols, and other topical creams. My dermatologist even considered putting me on accutane to which I refused. I became increasingly frustrated by the fact that not even prescription products were working for my skin so I began researching other products and I'm very glad I came across Obagi. Not only has it treated my acne but it has also helped cut back on my very oily skin. It even cleared up a patch on my jaw that I couldn't get rid of for months, even after my dermatologist injected it with cortisone shots. The 5% BP can be very drying, but if you (like me) are buying this product, your skin is probably already used to its fair share of harsh products. I went from using once a day to morning and night in less than a week and find that using a green tea moisturizer works great at preventing dryness and redness. It has by no means cured me from acne completely (much of my acne is hormonal), but it has worked better for me than any other over the counter or dermatologist prescribed product has and has freed me from embarassing skin. Would definitely recommend!

column13: It is so easy and convenient to use these little lip balm containers ...
column14: So I took the plunge to go all natural and make my own beauty and hygiene products over a year ago. It's really inexpensive but you have to buy casing for the products. I, bring a cheap person, would clean out old chapstick containers or little jars for my homemade natural lip balms. It takes forever and it's hard to fully clean old products out of the tubes and if I used a little jar I would need to apply the product with my finger or a brush-I work in a hospital so I was not able to apply the balms as frequently as I would have preffered due to not wanting to transfer germs... It is so easy and convenient to use these little lip balm containers not only because I don't have to clean out old products but they fit into my lifestyle of aiming to go all natural by using non toxic food grade plastic that is BPA free. I also really like that this product is made in the USA, big plus! These have made it easier to make my own cosmetic cover up as well as sunscreen on the go. It is also too easy to make separate batches of lip balm with a tingle of spearmint essential oil and give in a gift bag or peppermint infused balms as stocking stuffers. Everyone needs moistured lips, and making your own is a sweet gift idea. And 50 little tubes for only 15 buck is totally reasonable so my cheap self cam make a bunch for those quick go to grab gift bags and you legitly can give something that everyone will like. It has also been fun just to create tinted lip balms using crayons or even Hawaiian punch power mixed in since I have a solid stock of containers. It's just really nice to buy a good quality, very reasonably priced item without having to worry about cleaning old products or if it is even safe to use - I don't know for sure but are chapstick containers BPA free? I don't have to worry about these things-sound mind and not loosing sleep about my products or containers.

column6: Epic Dental 100% Xylitol Sweetened Gum
column14:
I bought this as an alternative to Trident and other sugar free gum because those were causing some... erm, unpleasant side effects, not too dissimilar from the Haribo Sugar-Free Gummy Bears. My pregnancy has been causing a bad taste in my mouth, and gum fixes that, except sometimes I end up chewing a pack a day.

I switched to xylitol based gum to see if that helped. So far, no side effects, but I'm going to try a different gum than this one. This gum loses its flavor after a couple minutes or less, then I feel like I'm chewing a piece of wax (like Chiclets gum). The taste, while it's there, is also very bland. It does its job, but it just can't match the juicy flavor of, say, Orbit's Strawberry Remix gum. That's super delicious.

As for the other reviews about this being "Made in China" or containing titanium dioxide... strangely the bottles I received had the "Made in China" label covered up with a sticker. Not sure why. But I don't care about titanium dioxide. It's found in virtually anything you consume that needs an opaque whiteness (paper, white paint, candies, toothpaste, dairy products, makeup, and so on). It doesn't cause cancer unless you're inhaling a lot of it as a powder (and, guess what, very fine sand, AKA silicon dioxide, will do that too). So I wouldn't worry about the titanium dioxide in this gum unless you intend to ground it into a very fine powder and snort it. In which case, you're a very silly person.

column6: Panasonic ES-LA63-S Arc4 Men's Electric Razor, 4-Blade Cordless with Wet/Dry Shaver Convenience
column13: A Significant Upgrade, But Not Without A Few Issues
column14:
Prior to this shaver, I had used a Phillips 2D Sensotouch shaver. The main problem I had with this shaver was the irritation it caused especially on my neck - every shave cause my neck to turn red and sometimes caused cuts. So with my purchase of this Panasonic, I was really looking for something that was much gentler on my face. 1 year later, here are some pro's and con's of what I've found.

Pros:
- Overall, the shaver is MUCH gentler on my face! Occasionally there are some problem spots on my face that require me going over the area a good number of times and this often causes a little irritation, but nothing as bad as with my previous shaver.
- The design of the shaver fits really well in my hand and is very comfortable to use!
- Travel case is pretty nice. It's not incredibly amazing, but it looks nice and seems pretty durable. Definitely handy when going on vacation.

Cons:
- The mechanism used to open the trimmer is not at all easy to engage. Sometimes it works and sometimes it doesn't, seeming like it is locked in place. Not a huge issue for me, as I don't use it much, but it can be an inconvenience.
- The battery life for this shaver leaves much to be desired. Personally, I don't get more than about 4-5 days of usage before the battery is dead, which is less than my previous shavers. Not awful, but if you forget to bring the charger on a trip, you might be in trouble.

column6: Ozone Layer Deodorant - The All Natural Oxygen Based Deodorant (Top Seller 3-pack)
column14:
This is the best deodorant. I've tried them all. When I came to realize the health risks associated with many others, on top of the fact that they stain clothing, I began to seek out healthier options. I was also under the impression, from using antiperspirant products since I was young, that I had a sweating disorder. I would sweat through the product, and sweat like crazy if i didn't use it. I found out that the antiperspirant was throwing my body's perspiration out of balance and causing me to sweat more. After a few months, I began to sweat a normal amount with regular deodorant. It would still stain clothes (not as much) and irritate the skin some (I'm glad I didn't go the prescription route). When I found out about the harmful chemicals going into all of our products, I began to do research and altered all the products that I use. Some were expensive and didn't work that well. Tom's worked and was a tolerable price, but would let odor through, and had to be reapplied. I finally decided to do extensive research online and find the best product for my needs once and for all; I am glad I did.
This seemed to be a fairly small business, so there wasn't information and reviews all over the place (which I hope will change, because this product should be everywhere), but the information and reviews I could find were very helpful, and 100% positive from everyone. It was two or three dollars more than name brand; however, one stick lasts three times longer than other products, so it is actually cheaper. You only need a small amount. It controls sweat in a healthy way (I haven't had one issue). It lasts all day. I've only used the coconut cream fragrance, and it smells great; not offensive at all. It only uses two natural ingredients, which are very healthy and good for your skin by themselves, and the ozone treatment makes a huge difference with them; also, it actually cleans, and is anti-bacterial, on top of being a great deodorant! I can't say enough good thingsabout this product. I hope to see many more products like this in the future for all of our needs; because, this one nailed it. I thank you to this company for doing such good work ^-^

column13: Something changed in the last year, tooth rush falls apart
column14: i have been buying these toothbrushes for years and years.  Love the rubber edges and sculpted bristles.  They were just right for a long time.  However, in the last year of buying, them, at first I thought I got a defective batch and kept buying them.  The rubber tines along the edge shear off constantly and you find rubber plugs in your mouth when you are brushing and spit.  I don't like spitting out toothbrush parts every time I brush my teeth.  All the rubber tunes break off one by one and the rubber grip coating on the toothbrush end, peels off too.  I'm tired of this newly cheapened quality, choking hazard toothbrush.  My teeth haven't changed any (ie, I'm not brushing braces or anything), so I don't know if they changed their manufacturing formulas but these don't work anymore.

column6: Crest Pro-Health HD Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Healthier Mouth via Daily Two-Step System - 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
column13: Two Minutes for Fresher, Whiter Teeth
column14:
I received a free full-sized Crest Pro-Health HD to try and review as part of a promotion.

I have been consistently using Pro-Health HD for over a month, and I'm satisfied with the result and am impressed with the amount of toothpaste and whitening gel that comes in the two tubes. I break down my review into the two main product benefits: cleaning and whitening.

Cleaning: 5/5 stars. The toothpaste (Step 1) cleans my teeth the best of any toothpaste I've used. My teeth feel clean and polished after the instructed one minute brushing, almost like leaving the dentist's office after a professional brushing/polishing. I'm left with a very fresh, minty mouth afterwards.

Whitening: 3/5 stars. As a casual coffee and tea drinker (one or two cups a day combined), my teeth tend to get minor stains, especially if I forget to drink water right after tea or coffee. The combination of the deep cleaning toothpaste and the whitening gel works to remove those minor stains and I can have another cup without feeling too guilty about it.

The whitening gel, however, works about the same as whitening strips. My teeth are slightly whiter, but not by much. Fortunately, the Crest Pro-Health HD kit is more affordable than the whitening strips or a professional whitening.

Overall: 4/5 stars. In just two minutes, I have a much cleaner mouth and teeth that feel polished, and the added bonus of a hint of whitening. Having to use two different products in one brushing isn't so bad once you get used to the routine. Also, like with most whitening strips, the first few times I used it my teeth and gums were a little sensitive for a few days, but everything feels fine now.

Finally, the sucralose ingredient in the whitening gel leaves an after-taste that's too sweet, but can be mitigated with a good water rinse.

For the price you pay, you get decent value out of the kit since you would end up paying much more money by buying a separate toothpaste and whitening strips. It's certainly worth a try. Maybe it'll keep you smiling.separate toothpaste and whitening strips. It's certainly worth a try. Maybe it'll keep you smiling.

column6: Surgi-Care Surgi-Wax Brazilian Wax Kit - 4.125 oz
column14:
First time waxer here, and i love this product!

Ok, now that we've gotten that out of the way, let me tell you more about the product.

This is a great product for first time waxers - pro waxing machines!

The only draw back that i found quite annoying, is that if your going to give yourself a full brazillian wax, and your not accustomed to doing it (or doing it quickly at least) then this is going to be a problem because this wax (as i'm sure ALL wax) gets cold/cool quick; and since its microwavable (to those who didnt know) that makes it a certain pain in the ass! You have to constatnly heat it up, which means getting uncomfortable, and running to the microwave, standing there to keep an eye on it, only to return to said position and wait for it too cool a bit, then apply a few times...repeat.

I still recommend it because its a good way to see if you actually want to go through and full out with the waxing process/life (before you buy all the kits etc. I would recommend the gigi kit (careful they have a few some with muslin strips&some without...) or the satin smooth kits (can be pricey, but worth it from what I've heard, although some people have posted they had allergic reactions to satin smooth so if you have sensitive skin--- beware) Just helpful information, so no one get upset! I'm not bashing any product, i think they are both great-- just trying to help someone who might be lost (like i was).

Good luck on your waxing journey!

column6: The Honest Company - Sunscreen Lotion SPF 30, 3 Fl Oz
column14:
I just bought two containers of the Honest Brand sunscreen in July 2015 and it worked great for us!! We live in the south and I used this sunscreen on my son for 2 weeks straight during his swim lessons (1 hour lesson in the morning @ 8:50am, plus time prior/after). The 2 weeks in July that I used this our UV index was 11 (extreme). My son NEVER burned or turned red. And, he is very pale, blond, blue eyes. We did use almost both whole containers just on him.

This sunscreen is getting some negative reviews lately, but it DOES work if used correctly. I am a research nut and find that this sunscreen does meet industry standards for an effective sunscreen.

My recommendation is that sunscreen should be your LAST line of defense, not your first!! Don't go out in the sun b/w 10am-2pm and wear protective clothing (hats, swim shirts, sunglasses, etc)! Also, apply before you go to the beach, not while out there! Apply a think layer! Remember that zinc oxide provides a physical barrier instead of a chemical barrier. Also, aim for a sunscreen with zinc oxide of 18% at the bare minimum and 25% as your maximum. Personally, I would not go above 25% zinc oxide as research in the EU (that I studied carefully) has not studied higher levels and there is always the chance for skin absorption. Also, in my opinion, if you have to reapply sunscreen more than once on your kids, you have them out in the sun for too long!! Some research has also shown that people who live in the north have higher rates of skin cancer. After living in both the north and south, I think this is because the summers are more tolerable in the north and you will be tempted to stay outside longer. In the south, the summers are too miserable to stay out for a great length of time. Plus, the south gets more sunshine throughout the year which helps maintain vitamin D levels. Just some things to consider...

The downside to this sunscreen: it does smell like play dough and it will stain (it did dye my son's white swim shirt a very pale beige). And, yes it will make you white....it has zinc oxide, hello!!

column6: Tom's of Maine Natural Deodorant Stick
column13: Decaying in quality and concern for customers.
column14: I used to love this type of deodorant and the company.  Hops and vegetable  propanediol was very safe and effective. Now ToM, now owned by Colgate, is using the same packaging and having the gall to call it original care but now using propylene glycol, a very common skin irritant.  I didn't notice the switch at first.  I thought my red and irritated armpits where because I had scraped myself with the plastic edge, or applied to much or sweated to much in the heat.  Then I finally checked the ingredients and realized what had happened.  I also had used the mountain spring which contains the original formula but is scented so I preferred the other. Now the mountain spring and some of the women's brands are the only ones that do not cause me a rash.  If you try to research this on ToM's website all you get is a page that acts like they are doing a you a favor for using natural gas-derived propylene glycol with no mention of it being entirely unnecessary.  Hops, scent free, pg-free, aluminum free used to be the standard and now does not exist within the company.  The best option I have is to compromise on the scent.  I am looking for another replacement though there  not  many options out there.  As soon as I can, however, I plan to leave the company behind.

column6: Philips Norelco 7700 Shaver
column13: Beautifully Made But Fails At Its Prime Directive.
column14:
I've never had great luck with electric shavers, but recent experience with a competing brand convinced me that there may be some merit in their use. After looking at the feature set and construction of the Norelco, I was excited to try it out. Unfortunately, it did not live up to my expectations.

Things started out well. I was impressed with the construction and look of the razor and love the fact that all three of the rotating heads pivoted independently of each other, something that my other three head razor does not do.

I also thought that the combination charging and washing system was fantastic. I like the way it looked, and like the idea of having the entire razor cleaned and lubricated after each use. Sadly, it was in critical areas of actual use that this razor showed its weakness on my beard.

In testing it I used it dry (which I found it fairly uncomfortable, not at all what I would think a razor for sensitive skin would feel like), wet with just water, with gels, and with traditional shaving creams. I used it regularly for 3 weeks, to make sure that I gave my skin ample time to acclimate to the new razor.

The results of all my testing were disappointing. I do have a fairly coarse beard, which has caused problems with electric razors in the past, but I thought that a razor carying this price tag would be able to handle it. No dice.

To get anywhere close to a reasonable shave, I had to apply more pressure than I found comfortable, and continue going over the same spots again and again and again; they felt irritated long before they were clean shaven. I tried it with less pressure to allow the blades time to conform to my face, but it made no difference at all and I was never able to get a suitably close shave with this razor.

The rest of the system worked flawlessly though, and I found it easy to clean, easy to charge and easy to hold onto wet or dry. For these reasons, I very much wanted the razor to be functionally excellent. Instead, I'll be going back to my older rotary razor which actually does a fine job even on my course beard, and I'll be passing this one along to my son who has very fine whiskers that are removed easily with the Norelco.

If this actually works on your beard, it's a wonderful razor with great construction look and feel. However if, like I, you have a course beard or simply one that just doesn't want to work with this guy, no amount of wonderful features will make up for the fact that you won't be clean shaven, and you'll be looking around for a traditional razor in no time.he razor to be functionally excellent. Instead, I'll be going back to my older rotary razor which actually does a fine job even on my course beard, and I'll be passing this one along to my son who has very fine whiskers that are removed easily with the Norelco.

If this actually works on your beard, it's a wonderful razor with great construction look and feel. However if, like I, you have a course beard or simply one that just doesn't want to work with this guy, no amount of wonderful features will make up for the fact that you won't be clean shaven, and you'll be looking around for a traditional razor in no time.

column13: Didn't work for me at all.
column14: I have color treated, dry, somewhat wavy hair that's prone to frizz.  I purchased this product because I was out of Wen and the sales associate assured me it would work equally well. I used the entire bottle because I didn't want to waste it, but I was happy to get back to my beloved Wen.  For me, there's absolutely no comparison of the two.  Wen leaves my hair light and shiny whereas No Poo left it heavy and unresponsive to styling.  I've heard that No Poo was developed for those with curly hair and although my hair is wavy, you'd think I'd be able to benefit as well.  But it's definitely not for me.  I've been using Wen for years and will continue to do so.  Leave No Poo to the curly headed among us.  It's really not suitable for those with wavy, medium fine hair.  Wen remains my favorite.

column6: Dove Men+Care Shower Tool, Active Clean 1 ct Pack of 4
column13: Always wanted to try one of these. Now that I did, no idea why.
column14:
I've seen these plentiful at my local department stores, as well as in the bathrooms of some family members. I've always used the cheapo loofahs you can get in bulk for a buck, and just got into the routine of replacing them when necessary.
Since I've seen Dove's tool ubiquitously, I've always wanted to try it out. I finally did, but now I'm waiting for the day it craps out so I can replace it with my old standard ones.

You see, I use regular bars of soap and the loofah to lather it up. The bars of soap are of usually better quality than body wash, not to mention are they cheaper in the long run and last longer. I simply use the loofah to scrub against the the bar of soap, build a lather, and use the loofah to wash my body without having to refill it.

With the Dove tool, you get half a loofah that doesn't maintain a lather very well. I always start with my top half, and by the time I reach my bottom half there is no soap to be found on the Dove tool. So I've gotten used to scrubbing the bars of soap on the other side of the tool, but that leaves little to no soap on my skin at all.

Also the plastic board containing the two halves is a bit difficult to hold and often slips off my hand when I'm scrubbing my body. Not only that, but there's no way this bulkier soap scrub can shrink, meaning you can't get into certain crevices, which is pretty necessary to have a fully clean body.

It's pretty expensive for what it is, and I'm sure it works for somebody, but in my experience it doesn't work well with me and my bars of soap. I'll stick with the regular loofahs, even though they tear apart sooner than desired.

column6: Alpha Hydrox Oil-Free Formula
column14:
really impressed with this product!

this is my first experience with a 10% glycolic AHA exfoliator and i wasn't sure what to expect. i'm still pretty young (30) but have started taking a serious interest in skin care for the last two years. i don't have wrinkles or many fine lines and was hoping this product would improve the overall texture and appearance of my skin. IT DID!

i use this product at night since the AHA can make skin sensitive to the sun (make sure you apply sunscreen liberally if you plan on being in the sun after application!! you skin will be more sensitive to burning and you can damage the delicate skin on your face.) i do not have sensitive skin so i had no problem with irritation, even applying after washing my face with other products.

the biggest difference i see is the appearance of my pores. i have always had sebaceous filaments on my nose & chin (dark "plugs" in pores - what most people confuse as blackheads.) even when i exfoliate and use facial masks - they are still visible. and the morning after using this product, their appearance is significantly diminished. not sure what is happening at a cellular level but this AHA very effectively dries them up and makes my pores looks so clear & clean. it also makes my skin so soft!

i let the product dry for about 10-15 minutes and then apply a p.m. moisturizer (CeraVe) mixed with a vitamin c/hyaluronic acid serum. my face looks and feel so nice the next day. (note: the moisturizer & serum probably absorb better after the affects of the AHA which is a plus but when i use this moisturizing mixture without the AHA, i definitely do not see the same results.)

not sure how long the bottle will last- i've had it for about 3 weeks and use it 2-4x per week. i still have (at least) half of a bottle left. the product is clear and a little runny and i use a dollop about the size of a quarter. i will continue to buy & use this product.

for the price and the results, it is worth every penny.for the price and the results, it is worth every penny.

column13: I like it but it won't replace my wash cloth
column14:
Lately I've been using Nivea Body Wash with a wash cloth instead of soap. I was intrigued by the reviews of this product which compare it to a luffa but not to a wash cloth (doesn't anybody use wash cloths anymore?).

First of all, something that was not clear to me from the product description nor the reviews: this is not Dove soap or body wash packaged inside a shower tool - you have to use some other product to make a lather, presumably a liquid body wash.

Compared to a wash cloth, it makes more efficient use of body wash - I find I need to use much less to maintain a good lather because I can pour the body wash into the "luffa side" of this and the liquid is held by the "pumice side" and rubber holder, which forms kind of a bowl.

I find myself wishing it had a long handle so I could scrub my back. I don't think this will replace my wash cloth but I do think I will look for a shower brush with a long handle.

column6: Dove Men+Care Hair Styling, Sculpting Paste 1.75 oz
column13: Just what I needed to finish my hair quickly and effectively in the morning.
column14:
I think my wife started me on Dove Men +care products though their soaps. BTW, they rock. First thing that I'd like to point out about ALL of Dove Men +care products is that they are in grey packaging in grey containers. They are subtle, direct, and something that I noticed and was attracted to, since I don't like to have neon products by my sink or shower to make me look like I want to be a 20 something. So - Dove marketing/packaging ppl... You did it right for me.

I have short straight hair that has little body on its own. My cut is a tight on the sides with a little more on the top, tapered on the back. I like a textured or stronger hold gel or pomade to develop more depth and style to the top and front and one that will hold through the day and may even be able to be reworked when life happens and it gets messed. All without looking like a slick shiny grease.

The Dove Men fortifying styling paste is a white dense paste that is easy to apply to the fingers to transfer to your hair. The white color means that it must be applied lightly, but its all that is really needed. The hold is immediate and provides a textured look when teasing a little. Its an all day hold and there is no strong scent to compete with your cologne. It's a solid paste and I recommend it highly. A little goes a long way, and depending on how aggressive you are with it, one of these could last between 1 to 2 months.

column6: Jergens Natural Glow Foaming Daily Moisturizer (Quick-Dry Formula), Medium to Tan Skin Tones, 6.25 Ounce
column14: I'm new to sunless tanners. I read reviews and found St. Tropez to be #1 recommended with 5 star reviews. Tried it many times, tried the mouse, oil, regular, and the express. I watched the demonstration video 4 times and followed the instructions exactly.  Pros: very tan, golden brown hands  Cons: messy, stains bathroom and clothing, towels, sheets, doesn't work no matter how many times I tried it, smells, mitts fall apart after 1 use, makes skin very dry, expensive. Did I say my hands were a pretty brown? :  Next I tried Clinique tanning lotion. Followed instructions exactly. Same problems as with St. Tropez, didn't work but got very tan hands.  All the time I'm going through the hassle of trying the above, sitting around for 8 hours in old clothes, exfoliating, showering with no luck my roommate kept saying "try Jergens". I was hesitant as it said it gives you a tan "gradually" and I wanted one instantly. I tried Jergens finally and am so glad I did!  Pros: no exfoliating, faint nice smell, easy to use, doesn't stain clothes or towels, sheets, bathroom floor, after 2 applications I had color, after 6 applications I have a gorgeous, natural, deep, dark, even brown tan, doesn't dry my skin, I shower then I use instead of lotion, dries in minutes, affordable, one tenth of price of other 2 I tried. Need I say more? I love this stuff! Wish I hadn't wasted 2 months trying the other stuff.  Cons: hard to find at store, often out of stock.  Just a suggestion, for my hands I wash them after applying to body, then I use a cotton ball and spray mouse on it, apply to hands and fingers then I use a Wet Wipe to wipe any excess off palms. So far hands look like the rest of my body and palms are not stained.

column13: If you like shaving with sandpaper, you'll love this razor!
column14:
OK. This razor is not as bad as shaving with sandpaper (not that I would actually know) but there are many instances when I use it that it catches my hair and is quite painful. Overall, it will give me a decent shave but it is not as smooth and painless as other electric razors I have used in the past.

The PR1235 (awesome name by the way) does a satisfactory job for the price. The main drawback for me is that you cannot run it under a sink to clean it. This makes cleaning a bit more bothersome and consequently it gets cleaned less frequently than other razors I have used.

If you are on a budget, this will do the job; I suggest you save $5-$10 more and get a slightly better model though.

column13: Awesome smell and smooth skin, but there are some cons I have......
column14:
I have decided to split my review into two categories - PROS and CONS, in order to hit some of my main points. As you can see I have given someONE's coffee body scrub a rating of three out of five, so feel free to read my full review in order to find out why!

----------
PROS
----------

~ As soon as I opened the bag I was greeted with a pleasant smell. The scrub smelled like fudge to me (weird....maybe my sense of smell is odd), but it was still amazing. While I applied the scrub to my whole body (along with the scrub's bag open) in the shower, I felt like I was in heaven haha.

~ I noticed and felt that my skin was smoother - it was so refreshing!

----------
CONS
----------

~ After using this scrub I wanted to reseal it, but it was quite difficult to do so. This was because of the excess of coffee body scrub along the seals. You'd have to wipe the seal with a slightly wet paper towel in order to close the bag properly. It would be easier to have some sort of circular container (or anything easier) instead of the bag.

~ When I applied the scrub and washed it off my body my skin was slightly itchy. I'm not sure if this is supposed to happen, but it did bother me quite a bit.

~ For 8oz of coffee body scrub, I do think this product should be cheaper. I was disappointed that the bag wasn't full, but of course the picture of the bag on this page clearly states how many ounces. Although I received this product at a discounted price in exchange for my honest and unbiased review, I believe the price should be $7-$8 instead of almost $15.

~~~~~
Overall, I have given someONE's coffee scrub with dead salt a rating of 3/5 stars. This is due to the negatives I have listed. If the product could be improved in some ways (for example a larger oz for $15/cheaper price for an 8 oz, replace scrub's bag with an easier container in order to grab the scrub or open + close it, etc) then I'd love to purchase this scrub again.c) then I'd love to purchase this scrub again.

column6: Neutrogena Healthy Skin Blush
column13: Soft tones, easy to blend for a natural look
column14:
The Neutrogena Blush is available in 5 colorsâ€”3 blush tones, a bronzer, and an illuminating powder. I am using the rosy blush, the bronzer, and illuminator.

The rosy color is a soft, subtle tone, perfect for my fair skin. I applied the powder using a soft brush, and one or two passes is all I need for a natural look. The color will deepen with an additional application. The bronzer and the illuminating powder both blend well with this color. The bronzer tones down the color, and the illuminator gives it a nice glow. The bronzer has a nice look on its own, but the illuminating powder looked best over the rosy blush. All three of these have good staying power and last all day without needing a touch-up.

Because this is a soft powder, it brushes up easily when I sweep my brush across it, similar to a loose powder. It can be a little messy, but I prefer the softer look it creates over that of a hard pressed powder. Plus it's easier to blend a softer product.

I like the blush and the way it looks and feels; however, I'm not crazy about the plastic case it is packaged in. The cases are very difficult to open, and while this is a plus when carrying them in a purse or make-up bag, it's frustrating to fight with them when I'm in a hurry in the morning.

column6: Philips Norelco Rq12+ Replacement Head For Series 8000 (Sensotouch 3D) And Arcitec
column14:
I have had the new RQ12+ for several months now and have waited to make sure that this product is given a fair review. This is a great replacement to the original RQ12 razor head, which has been discontinued. All of the complaints about poor quality, tugging on your beard, loud noises, the razor losing its sharpness after a few weeks, etc. etc., is simply not true. In a nut shell, here are the "Joe Friday" facts:
Pros: 1. Very sharp blades. 2. Excellent pivoting action of each razor head, despite the fact that the three heads are seated as one unit on the pod. Each blade assembly pivots quite well and independent of each other. 3. The blades are very sharp and remain sharp even after three months of use with a heavy beard. 4. Cleaning is easy and more thorough then the previous RQ12 head. The entire 3-blade assembly unit pops off to be cleaned under hot running water, then simply snapped back on. 5. The blades are very sharp, resulting in no pulling or tugging. If there is pulling or tugging of your beard, you are using too much pressure. A light touch is all that is necessary. 6. The sharp blades and excellent pivoting action result in a comfortable shave and smooth skin. Hint: Use Williams Lectric shave.
Cons: 1. A little more noisy than the RQ12. Why? Because its cutting more hair. 2. A little cheaper looking plastic. 3. No more hinges on the blade assembly for cleaning. You must now remove the entire head assembly, but this means the cleaning is now more thorough. The cosmetic issues are relevant to a great shave.

column6: Vichy Dercos Anti Dandruff Sulphate Free Shampoo 200ml
column13: She recommended the product herself after suffering from severe scalp psoriasis ...
column14: Bought this shampoo for my wife who suffers from chronic scalp psoriasis with itching & flaking.  What was most influential in our decision to purchase this particular brand came from an YouTuber that goes by Ellko.  She recommended the product herself after suffering from severe scalp psoriasis for most of her life.  This was a life-changing product for Ellko after having tried countless products to overcome this affliction.  The same is true for my wife.  My wife also color-treats her hair, so we decided to go with the Sulphate/Sulfate-Free version & hoped that it would work just as well as the original formula.  My wife used the shampoo for the first time 2 nights ago after suffering through a particularly bad case of itchiness, redness,flaking & inflammation.  She experienced some soreness while shampooing due to the state in which her scalp was in, but nothing long lasting or unlike anything she felt using other shampoos.  The scent itself was light & fresh--no foul chemical-like smells.  In the past, after using other shampoos, she would still see patches of redness & flakiness around her hairline--this time there was none to be found & by the next day, the symptoms would usually be back & she would have small crusty patches all over her scalp.  NOT THIS TIME!  Here it is, 2 days after shampooing & her scalp is virtually flake-free & itch-free!  WHAT A MIRACLE!!  We will definitely be re-purchasing this shampoo!  A couple cons:  The bottles only contain 200ml which would probably last my wife maybe 3-4 shampoos....maybe.  She has thick, long hair that hits the middle of her back, so this is quickly going to become a pricey solution to her problem.  Which brings me to the next problem....the price....YIKES!!  There's got to be a cheaper way to purchase this shampoo.  I will have to research elsewhere to hopefully find it cheaper.

column14:
You know I was going to buy this on Amazon and am a fan of full size bottles in general.But K-Mart had the 1.7oz size on sale for $12.49.A pretty good deal as I snatched up the last two at my local store.But I still recommend Amazon for being well priced so I will be back here for the full size.So,it's nice to see alot of people praising this 70s scent but others say "what does this cologne smell like"? a good question.I can't speak for other individuals but here's my opinion from wearing this on and off as an occasional buy throughout the years.

Lagerfeld Classics Scent:
To me the scent of this cologne is dry cedar wood,orange teased with some kind of spice,and vanilla powder.There is a minty quality that dies down into a green/herbal accord that's very faint...I'm guessing basil.All of this sits on top a bed of tobacco and smells pretty rich.Everything pretty much changes hands as the cedar and tobacco becomes more dominant and the sweetness becomes very light.I don't consider Lagerfeld to be ultra masculine where animal musk notes and darker woods and spices would lend more ruggedness and depth.It's a good cologne and comes off as very natural on dry down.in my opinion Lagerfeld Classic runs very cool and is friendly to wear year round.

I drift from this cologne eventually in desire for a rich scent on dry down but something about Lagerfeld always reels me back in.

column14:
OMG !!!!!!! I have been cruising Amazon for this exact item for quite some time and was thrilled to see it for an excellent price. I had been to retail and beauty supply stores everywhere I went, only to be told I could not order just the unit. I had already purchased extra rollers with my original unit. My Caruso Steam Unit gave up the after some major miles, through many hair styles.
I have very thick, straight American Indian hair that was prematurely gray hair before I could graduate high school. I purchased the Caruso Steam set and many extra curlers years ago when it first came on the market. I had tried various kinds of steam roller sets that were difficult to wrap my straight hair around. They were pokey and heavy with painful steel pins to hold rollers in my hair; only for the curls to fall out almost immediately. I tried ceramic, adjustable heat settings, and many different curling irons and dryers that was new on the market. I combined hair gels or mousse with them only to have curls and waves fall out within minutes. I went to beauty school (lol) after high school. Really not my thing
The new unit I received is not round like this picture. It is kidney shaped.
The old version I had to add a small amount of salt to the water.
The newer version has a slider switch for OFF, STEAM and IONIC STEAM.
I love, love, love the Caruso Steam for my hair.
I used 6-8 curlers for my whole head.
Literally seconds to put each in and about the time I get them all in it is time to take them out. Just like my old Caruso Steam unit (without the salt).
My curls last three days minimum.
I DO NOT use hair products on my hair ever.
Curls are soft and natural feeling.
Caruso Steamer does not damage hair. Stopped perms many years ago after finding this steamer. This amazing steamer adds shine to my curls. I can run my fingers through my hair as much as I want.
There is never those bent ends of hair, curls just fall, I shake my head, move a curl or two with my fingers and I am out the door.
I have missed this little time saver and am continually complimented on my hair and how much younger I look.
I hope this helps someone, lets me know how you use your Caruso Steamer

column6: 14k Yellow OR White Gold SOLID 1.1mm Box Link Chain Necklace with Lobster Claw Clasp
column13: Good chain, but still pulls hair
column14:
I only wear box link chains like this one because I have incredibly fine hair that gets caught in other chains. My hair does get caught in this one, though not nearly as badly as other chain types (which will yank out entire locks if I have my hair down). In particular, the clasp links on this box chain like to grab my hair. (By the clasp links, I mean the single links connecting the clasp, not the clasp itself.)

But this is good quality chain. The lobster clasp is solid and works well. It's stamped with 585 (14K gold) and LGD. I got the 16in length/1mm width because I have a small neck and like little dangly pendants. The chain hangs well and has a substantial weight.

column6: JewelrieShop Clip On Hoops, Clip On Earrings Fake Earrings Non-Piercing Spring Hoop Earrings for Sensitive Ears Fake Cartilage Earrings
column13: Lightweight, comfortable, 3 & 9 yr olds LOVED and wore them well
column14: These are so lightweight and wonderful.  both my granddaughters, ages 3 and 9, have pierced ears which have partially to completely closed up because they hated to change out their pierced earrings.  It was a constant fight.  I guess they have ear issues, or perhaps it hurt a few times and they're just afraid.  My 9 yr old grand daughter has hated them since age 2, so it's just carried over to her current age.  NO WAY either of them want their ears re-pierced...so no cute earrings EVER.  Sadness in a family of jewelry loving gals, needless to say.  ENTER THE SPRING HINGE CLIP ONS!  These things are amazing.  Neither of my grandkids could even feel me putting them on, and of course, they LOVED THEM!  The spring hinges on the back open so easily and smoothly, and they are gentle on the backs of the ears.  My 3 year old grand daughter did complain after a couple of hours that she wanted them off, but she didn't touch them the entire two hours before that.  I think both of them forgot they had them on, except for the occasional admiring themselves in the mirror from time to time.  I'm back looking for more styles now that I know how well they work.

column6: Hot Pumpkin Locket Necklace Perfume Fragrance Essential Oil Aromatheraâ€‹py Diffuser
column13: Loving how cute and little this is
column14:
With one of my favorite parts of Cinderella being the beautiful coach when I saw this locket I couldn't pass it up. This is actually a very small locket and I will say smaller than I thought it would be. That makes this even better than I hoped it would be. There is some very intricate work with this piece and it is very hard to tell where the welds are. The locket does open easily and closes securely so that the little fuzz ball doesn't fall out when you are wearing it. It does look pretty empty so that is an option if you don't want to wear any scent or just want something that looks pretty. The inserts hold roughly 2-3 drops of essential oils and the scent does last most of the day.

Now if you do choose to use the small inserts, fuzz balls, they hold roughly 2-3 drops of essential oils or fragrance. I have found that depending on the strength of the fragrance is equal to how long the scent will last. I actually prefer to use essential oils with this so the scent lasts longer. Since perfume tends to have a high level of alcohol it does fade quickly.

Overall this is absolutely adorable and I wear it as often as I can, with or without the insert. It is a beautiful piece, has held up to every day wear, and looks good.

column6: Teacher Gifts for Women Floating Locket Keychain Full of Teacher Charms, Teacher Appreciation Gifts
column13: Great Token to start the school year off right!
column14: Every year the start of school seems to get a little harder for me and my sons. To me it's a signal that summer is almost over, and the long nights of sleep overs and bonfires come to a close. So each year I try to always get my child one small, special token to keep to remind them of that year in school. I want them to be able to look back when they are older on their little box of tokens and tell their kids how special their child life was. So I found the Back to School locket Keychain from a Touch of Dazzle, to be a super cute and appropriate tocken. The Locket  keychain is made with such detail, and has an adorable look to it. It is very heavy made, and I don't worry about it coming off my sons bookbag because it has a durable clip. The charms that move inside of the keychain locket are so detailed and little just like the items they replicate. I feel like this locket keychain will be something my son will look back on in many years and still enjoy looking at it. I absolutely love this product. I received this product at a discount price in exchange for my honest, unbiased review. The price however does not affect my opinion of the product.

column6: QIANSE \Butterfly Love\" Pendant Necklace Swarovski Crystals Necklace with Birthstones Jewelry for Women Xmas Gifts for Women Birthday Gifts for Women Sister Friend Anniversay Gifts for Her"
column14:
Gorgeous light blue crystal, teardrop necklace with three hearts above, one of which has embedded clear crystals in it. I LOVE this necklace, sparkling yet not overpowering. The multi-faceted teardrop crystal is approximately 3/4" long.

When you first open up this necklace you may think that the chain is really twisted. (We did!) HOWEVER once you actually look at it more carefully you realize that it is double fine chain and is actually deliberately twisted around the bottom and top hearts. SO don't try to untwist these as you will end up with a pendant that is carefree! The chain is approximately 15" so sits high up on your chest.

The necklace is presented in a quality gift box and once opened you will find it in sealed plastic inside. Mine came with a FREE, very pretty silk-like scarf (approximately 18" x 19") included in a separate box in the sealed package. The coloring of the scarf is mostly reds and greens on a white background - floral pattern.

PLEASE remember this is fashion jewelry. Although silver/white gold in color, it is actually only white gold plated. If you are looking for a new necklace for yourself OR as a gift this would be a great option for you! Product was received in exchange for an honest review. Thanks, Liz

I like the necklace, but it is a little strange

Pros:
- Nice and sold, heavy duty and feels nice
- The chain is sufficiently long at 24 inches long
- The "bullet" is 1.75 inches long and 3/4 inch wide and very attractive

Cons:
- It unscrews, maybe a little too easily. There is no reason it needs to unscrew, except perhaps to hide a small amount of some illegal substance. It does allow you to prove it isn't an object that could actually be fired from a gun. This is good because...
- You can't take any weapons paraphernalia through the airport. People have had family jewelry/heirlooms taken away by TSA because they are in the shape of a gun or bullet. Most notably was some woman's necklace that was a tiny silver gun. It couldn't fire, but they still detained her.

I received this item as sample for review, either free or at a discount. I am keeping it for permanent personal use. These are my honest thoughts. 2015-08-03 US 7583138 R3FRFW6TJVCK31 B00FORV99K 763597894 Pro Jewelry \"Passport\" Dangling Bead Charm for Snake Chain Charm Bracelet"

column13: FUN and FANCY -- for a younger woman
column14:
These are unique, stylish looking bracelets, that will appeal to a younger woman. Its hard to see from the photo, but a black nylon web is filled with "Austrian Crystals" (Quartz? polymer crystals?) that are tinted into different colors. The silver clasp is magnetic, so its easy to close around your wrist. The double wrapped bracelet, could be uncoiled and worn around your neck as a torus necklace, if you're neck is slender enough. FancyDeli produces high end costume jewelry, with a stylish European flair. Older women will not gravitate to the style. Nevertheless, teenage girls, and young women in their 20s or even 30s, would find this to be very practical for adding an air of elegance to casual wear, or to accessorize with their evening wear. If you have issues with wearing metal bracelets, but are looking for something more fun and fancy that a plastic hoop, this might be a choice or you.
I was provided a free bracelet in exchange for a fair and honest review.

column6: Christmas Gifts, Heart Shaped Corundum Copper Tennis Bracelet for Women, upcoming black Friday deals, Fashion Jewelry (Sapphire)
column14:
The sapphire colored crystals are a little darker in person than what is shown on the screen. This bracelet has a delicate look to it with each cluster having the blue center crystal with a number of clear ones surrounding it. Each of the heart crystals is "clawed" in, set similar to a ring. There are 23 heart clusters on this 7 1/4" length bracelet with an extra trio of heart clusters and clasp enclosed for extra length if required. Each heart cluster is approximately 5/16".

How easy is it to get on? This bracelet is a little tougher than some to get on but I can manage it by myself without assistance. The bracelet is presented in a quality gift box and once opened you will find the bracelet in a sealed plastic bag inside.

Mine came with a FREE, very pretty silk-like scarf (approximately 18" x 19") included in a separate box in the sealed package. The coloring of the scarf is mostly reds and greens on a white background - floral pattern.

PLEASE remember this is fashion jewelry. Although silver/white gold in color, it is actually only white gold plated. If you are looking for something a little different, dainty but with some color then this could well be the bracelet for you! Product was received in exchange for an honest review. Thanks, Liz

column6: Opal with Pink, White and Blue Charms - Fits Pandora Charms Bracelet
column14:
I have a charm bracelet that I have recently been updating, and adding more charms to. I loved the look of this charm, and I added it onto my bracelet. It fit on my bracelet perfectly, not too tight, not too loose. The charm is covered in swarvoski crystals, most of them being white. There are a few random pink and blue crystals mixed in as well. Finally there are 3 larger crystals, 2 that are a pink opal color, and one that is a white opal color (I'm not sure if this pattern is the same with all the charms, or if it is randomly chosen). The crystals are very shiny and add a nice bling to my bracelet. The pops of color on it is nice as well!

For the cons, the charm has some beautiful pink and blue crystals on it, however they are awkwardly placed. I would have really liked if the colors were more strategically placed, perhaps with a different pattern. Overall though, it is a very nice, pretty charm! So far I have not experienced any crystals coming loose, nor were any missing upon arrival.

Please note that I was sent this product complimentary to try out in my home in order to share my honest experience, thoughts and review.

column6: Qianse \Tree of Life\" Rose Gold Plated Copper Pendant Necklace Cubic Zirconia"
column13: The tree of life is rich in symbolism, this would make a thoughtful gift
column14: I have this necklace in the rose gold plated, and it's very beautifully detailed.  The tree of life represents different things to different people.  It's been representative of protection, healing, knowledge, family, immortality and good-just to name a few.  It's symbolism goes back hundreds of years and spans many religions and cultures.  The chain of the necklace has a lobster claw clasp that's small, but easy to fasten, and measures 18" with a 2" extender, so 20" total.  The pendant has a a bit over a 1/2" drop, not as big as 3/4".  It's small, but seems to be well made, the stones are inset well and it has a moderate amount of sparkle. It's smaller than it looks on the model in the photo, and that's actually a good thing in this case. I received it free in exchange for my honest review.

column6: Mens Stainless Steel Pill Cross Necklace Pendant - Black & Silver, 21\ Inches Chain"
column14:
The overall build quality of the container is pretty good and it does seem sturdy, but because accurate dimensions are not given in the description it was too small for even the small pills (Oxycodone-generic) we were carrying for a sick friend.

So here are some dimensions measured with a calipers:
ID (Inside Diameter) of the smaller (black) part: 0.225\\\ / 5.73mm
Depth of black part, shoulder to end: 0.491\\\\\" / 12.48mm
Length of chain: ~20.5\\\\\"
ID (Inside diameter) of attached fixed ring: 0.103\\\\\" / 2.62mm

I got this because another comment said the ID was 1/4\\\\\" which would have been large enough, but it is actually a bit smaller so measure your pills carefully.

Honestly, while the rating may seem a little harsh, when you are selling something to be used as a container and don't include accurate dimensions it is about the same as a defective product. Would you want to buy a box or a suitcase if the dimensions were given as descriptions (\\\\\"There is a little room for storage....\\\\\" ???) or only irrelevant (outside) dimensions were given? Yea, me neither.

So now you have it: *Inside* dimension of the smaller black section: 0.225\\\\\" x 0.491\\\\\".

Measure twice and good luck."

column13: I have some ideas myself for possibly making an even better, more comfortable and stylish pressure earrings but for ...
column14: My daughter had surgery to remove kiloids from both her earlobes several years ago, we were told to use pressure earrings to keep scarring down. I have some ideas myself for possibly making an even better, more comfortable and stylish pressure earrings but for now these are the best I've found so far. I will admit over time the constant opening and closing of putting them on and taking them off, the integrity of the earring  becomes compromised and you will have to replace them in 1 or 2 month. If this company can somehow make a more sturdy earring, that applies more pressure  I would probably refer alot more business their way. But for now they are the best I've tried so far.

column14: This seller rocks! Item's delivery date was estimated 24 plus days but arrived in just 7days and shipping was free! The cross is of good quality and looks way more expensive than even the regular price would dictate. My only issue is that it's a little long for my taste, but not too long too appear "gangsta". The chain is also nice, but wouldnt you know just a little short in length for my personal taste! The seller also gave me a unique pendant and 2 black cord type chains at no cost! It's very cool. Although I always read reviews before purchasing anything I never write them (this is the first). I felt everyone should know about the seller AND the quality and value of this cross.

column13: Anatometal: Expensive Body Jewelry--Not Even Nickel Free
column14:
First, let me say I am allergic to nickel. Itâ€™s not an extreme allergy, but itâ€™s more than enough to be a pain. Especially when it comes to jewelry which is almost impossible to get in silvertoned metals without nickel.
So, I did research on Anatometal and it is approved by the Association of Professional Piercers and is considered suitable even for fresh piercings. Nothing put up a red flag that its implant grade stainless steel might contain nickel. I have even worn implant grade stainless steel in this, a fully healed piercing Iâ€™ve had for a long time, and other piercings without issue.
When I got the rings, I decided to just try the first one after doing all the appropriate stuff to ensure no problems. Immediately, my ear started to swell and itch. Quickly, I removed the piercing and put my old jewelry back in.
Later, I found (courtesy of the seller, Steel Navel) that after clicking after link which then you have to find another link, and then yet another link on Anatometalâ€™s website that â€œsome people do have allergies to the nickel found in the metal [implant grade stainless steel]â€, but that the â€œprotective layer of chromium oxide that helps keep the nickel content trapped inside [the jewelry]â€. I sure hope medical grade metal implants are nickel free if I ever have to get one!
Nickel allergies are very common. So common the European Union doesnâ€™t allow nickel in jewelry products. Itâ€™s well known nickel allergies can be caused by nickel exposure. We shouldnâ€™t be putting that stuff in our bodies, regardless of what kind of â€œcoatingâ€ it had on it.
In my opinion, Anatometal is overpriced and you donâ€™t even get a nickel free product. A fact that is not easily found on their website. If you are allergic or even sensitive to nickel I would strongly suggest you stay far away from Anatometalâ€™s stainless steel body jewelry.
As for me, this completely ruined my experience with Anatometal jewelry forever. I will never try another Anatometal product again.

column13: Excellent quality, but store the necklace by hanging or the chain becomes impossibly tangled!!
column14: I wear this necklace a lot, it's the perfect size and sparkle for me.  I received it free in exchange for my honest review.I have the sterling silver version, which has two hearts; the inner is solid silver and engraved with "LOVE YOU FOREVER", and the outer heart is rimmed with two bands of shimmering crystals. If you don't care for the engraving, the little heart stays nestled in the big one (as pictured) while you're wearing it, so you don't actually ever see the engraving.  Even if you pull the two hearts apart, they just fall back together.  Chain lobster claw clasp is easy to fasten, but the clasp is moderately small.  Chain length is 17" with a 2" drop, so 19" total. pendant drop is just between 1/2" and 3/4".  This necklace could easily pass for a diamond necklace, because the crystals are small and shimmering; definitely a keeper! It comes in a standard paper gift box, and mine had a scarf/pocket square gift included. The only problem I found with this necklace, is that mine became terribly tangled if I didn't store it hanging.

The multi-faceted teardrop crystal is approximately 5/8" long. The chain is approximately 16" long with an extra length if you need it. The necklace is presented in a quality gift box and once opened you will find it in a sealed plastic bag inside. In a separate box in the sealed outer package is a very pretty blue silk-like scarf (approximately 18" x 19").

PLEASE remember this is fashion jewelry. Although the color of white gold it is only white gold plated.

column13: For the price, this is a really good ring!
column14: I  bought this as a gift for myself, as there was a really great sale on Amazon Curated rings right before the holidays. My review is heavily weighed on the phenomenal price I paid. Upon its arrival, I admit I was initially disappointed, as this is pave style, and when placed next to my three stone wedding band there is a difference between the quality, as obviously this is made up of many tiny stones vs. larger cut ones. My wedding ring and bands are obviously much more expensive as well. However, after adjusting to recognizing that they are two different styles, I am more and more impressed with my purchase. I wear it as a right hand ring, and it does sparkle wrote a bit. From afar, it looks as if it is made up of larger, more expensive stones. I wear this ring everyday, so clearly I have learned to appreciate it more and more. I am very happy that I purchased it! It was a great deal and I see similar ones advertised in the department store for twice the price.

column14: I received the rose gold toned necklace. While I own plenty of jewelry, I do not own many crosses. The chain itself is just your basic silver-toned chain, the cross itself though is the "shinning star" of the necklace. I will first say I was a little surprised by the color as it is more gold than rose gold in my opinion. Nonetheless, I think the cross is a really pretty piece and the silver-toned circle in the middle of the cross makes it come all together to form a really nice piece. I think the price for the piece is justified and a good deal. I think it is not only a great piece for those that enjoy crosses, but it makes a great gift as well and I plan to purchase them as gifts in the future.

column6: INCLUDES 16g - Ear Stretching Kit Steel Tunnels Tapers 00g 0g 2g 4g 6g 8g 10g 12g 14g 16g Gauges Plugs PLUS Instructions
column14:
I just received my product in the mail and am very pleased with it! After ordering I requested from the seller for each set of tapers and tunnels be labeled so I can identify them, and as requested, each set came in individual bags with labels. The package also came with instructions for taking care of different material plugs and a guide to stretching ears with wait times included.
I'm also so glad I chose this set as it was the only set I could find with 16g tapers included! When I saw how small 16g was, I tried to use the 14g tapers and plugs (which is what most sets start you off with) but once I felt too much pressure I decided to start with the 16g. As I suspected, My holes were too small to start with 14g and I didn't want to risk damaging my ears.
As I said, I'm very pleased with my product. It came with all the pieces listed in the description (which, after reading other reviewers who said they thought they were missing pieces or had received double, was another reason I requested my tapers and tunnels be individually labeled.) I hope to do business again with this seller in the future. Thank you!

column14:
These are pretty pearls, just the right size, and I love the pale pink color. I wear them every day. They are small enough to be unobtrusive, but large enough to show off.
I had them on my wish list because I love pearls, but can't afford the high-end ones, so when the priced dropped drastically, I bought them immediately.
I'm not taking them out before showering, or wiping them down like you're supposed to, but they've held up very well over the past month. I'm sensitive to other metals, and can only wear real gold in my ears, and these have not itched or irritated my ears at all.
For inexpensive pearls, I think they're a great buy.
